{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01CeFYNNBMDRZ2oNQzZVd3n7","type":"tool_result","content":"   100→\n   101→### Signer Model\n   102→\n   103→One server keypair for MVP, loaded from environment (`SERVER_KEYPAIR`). This keypair:\n   104→- Co-signs `create_match` transactions (appears as `server: Signer` in the instruction)\n   105→- Pays the settlement transaction fee (~0.000005 SOL per settle)\n   106→- Does NOT need to be the same key that calls `settle` (settle is permissionless — anyone\n   107→  with the secret can call it), but using the server key simplifies operational monitoring\n   108→\n   109→Future: split into separate signing authority (cold, for create) and settlement authority\n   110→(hot, for settle). The on-chain program already supports this — `settle` has no server\n   111→signer constraint.\n   112→\n   113→### Transaction Flow\n   114→\n   115→```\n   116→Player                    Backend                     Chain\n   117→  │                          │                          │\n   118→  ├─ POST /create ──────────►│                          │\n   119→  │  {tier, side, wallet}    │                          │\n   120→  │                          │─ generate secret         │\n   121→  │                          │─ commitment = sha256()   │\n   122→  │                          │─ build create_match tx   │\n   123→  │                          │─ server partial-sign     │\n   124→  │                          │─ store secret in DB      │\n   125→  │◄─ {tx, matchPda} ───────│                          │\n   126→  │                          │                          │\n   127→  ├─ co-sign + submit ─────────────────────────────────►│\n   128→  │                          │                          │─ create match PDA\n   129→  │                          │                          │\n   130→  │         ... opponent joins (user-submitted) ...     │\n   131→  │                          │                          │─ PHASE_LOCKED, target_slot set\n   132→  │                          │                          │\n   133→  │                          │◄── poll / subscription ──│\n   134→  │                          │─ wait for target_slot    │\n   135→  │                          │─ build settle tx         │\n   136→  │                          │─ submit settle ─────────►│\n   137→  │                          │                          │─ verify commitment\n   138→  │                          │                          │─ derive result\n   139→  │                          │                          │─ pay winner\n   140→  │                          │                          │─ emit MatchSettled\n   141→  │                          │                          │\n   142→  │                          │─ update DB (settled)     │\n   143→```\n   144→\n   145→### Database Schema\n   146→\n   147→Two tables — `rounds` for state, `operator_events` for append-only audit trail.\n   148→\n   149→#### `rounds`\n   150→\n   151→| Column | Type | Notes |\n   152→|--------|------|-------|\n   153→| `pda` | `TEXT PRIMARY KEY` | Base58 match PDA address |\n   154→| `game` | `TEXT NOT NULL` | `'coinflip'` (extensible later) |\n   155→| `creator` | `TEXT NOT NULL` | Base58 creator wallet |\n   156→| `server_key` | `TEXT NOT NULL` | Base58 server pubkey used |\n   157→| `secret` | `BYTEA NOT NULL` | 32-byte server secret |\n   158→| `commitment` | `BYTEA NOT NULL` | SHA256(secret) |\n   159→| `tier` | `SMALLINT NOT NULL` | Tier index |\n   160→| `side` | `SMALLINT NOT NULL` | Creator's chosen side |\n   161→| `nonce` | `BIGINT NOT NULL` | Match nonce |\n   162→| `phase` | `TEXT NOT NULL` | `created`, `locked`, `settling`, `settled`, `expired` |\n   163→| `target_slot` | `BIGINT` | Set when match transitions to locked |\n   164→| `settle_tx` | `TEXT` | Settlement tx signature |\n   165→| `settle_attempts` | `INT DEFAULT 0` | Retry counter |\n   166→| `result_hash` | `BYTEA` | 32-byte result (post-settlement) |\n   167→| `result_side` | `SMALLINT` | 0=Heads, 1=Tails (post-settlement) |\n   168→| `winner` | `TEXT` | Base58 winner address (post-settlement) |\n   169→| `created_at` | `TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT now()` | |\n   170→| `updated_at` | `TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT now()` | |\n   171→\n   172→#### `operator_events`\n   173→\n   174→| Column | Type | Notes |\n   175→|--------|------|-------|\n   176→| `id` | `BIGSERIAL PRIMARY KEY` | Auto-increment |\n   177→| `pda` | `TEXT` | Nullable — some events are system-level |\n   178→| `event_type` | `TEXT NOT NULL` | `secret_generated`, `tx_built`, `match_detected`, `settle_submitted`, `settle_confirmed`, `settle_failed`, `settle_retried`, `timeout_detected` |\n   179→| `payload` | `JSONB` | Event-specific data |\n   180→| `created_at` | `TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT now()` | |\n   181→\n   182→**Indexes**: `rounds(phase)` for settlement worker queries, `rounds(creator)` for lookup,\n   183→`operator_events(pda, created_at)` for round history, `operator_events(event_type, created_at)` for monitoring.\n   184→\n   185→---\n   186→\n   187→## Functional Requirements\n   188→\n   189→<!-- FR acceptance criteria checkboxes are audited by /gap-analysis after completion.\n   190→     Each checkbox gets an HTML comment annotation: satisfied/deferred/gap with evidence. -->\n   191→\n   192→### FR-1: Secret Generation & Transaction Signing\n   193→\n   194→The service generates a cryptographically secure secret, computes the commitment,\n   195→builds a `create_match` transaction with the server's partial signature, and returns it\n   196→to the requesting wallet for co-signing and submission.\n   197→\n   198→**Endpoint**: `POST /fairness/coinflip/create`\n   199→\n   200→**Request body**:\n   201→```json\n   202→{\n   203→  \"wallet\": \"<base58 creator pubkey>\",\n   204→  \"tier\": 3,\n   205→  \"side\": 0,\n   206→  \"nonce\": 42,\n   207→  \"timestamp\": 1710000000,\n   208→  \"signature\": \"<base58 Ed25519 signature over canonical payload>\"\n   209→}\n   210→```\n   211→\n   212→**Response** (200):\n   213→```json\n   214→{\n   215→  \"transaction\": \"<base64 serialized partial tx>\",\n   216→  \"matchPda\": \"<base58 PDA address>\",\n   217→  \"commitment\": \"<hex commitment>\"\n   218→}\n   219→```\n   220→\n   221→**Acceptance Criteria:**\n   222→- [ ] Secret is 32 bytes generated via Node.js `crypto.randomBytes(32)` (CSPRNG)\n   223→- [ ] Commitment is computed using the same algorithm as `packages/fairness/src/commitment.ts` (`sha256(secret)`)\n   224→- [ ] Transaction is built using the coinflip IDL (`create_match` instruction) with correct accounts and args\n   225→- [ ] Server keypair partially signs the transaction (server appears as `server: Signer`)\n   226→- [ ] User's wallet is set as fee payer — server pays zero on-chain cost for creation\n   227→- [ ] Secret is stored in the `rounds` table keyed by match PDA before the response is returned\n   228→- [ ] An `operator_events` entry of type `secret_generated` is written\n   229→- [ ] Match PDA is derived using seeds `[\"match\", creator, nonce.to_le_bytes()]` matching the on-chain program\n   230→- [ ] If the same PDA already exists in the DB (duplicate nonce), the endpoint returns 409 Conflict\n   231→- [ ] Recent blockhash is fetched at request time (transaction expires naturally via Solana's ~60s blockhash window)\n   232→\n   233→### FR-2: Settlement Worker\n   234→\n   235→A background process that detects locked matches and submits settlement transactions\n   236→once entropy is available.\n   237→\n   238→**Acceptance Criteria:**\n   239→- [ ] Worker polls the chain (via `getProgramAccounts` or equivalent) for `CoinflipMatch` accounts in `PHASE_LOCKED` where the `server` field matches the service's keypair\n   240→- [ ] For each locked match, worker checks if `target_slot` has been reached (current slot >= target_slot)\n   241→- [ ] Worker retrieves the stored secret from the `rounds` table using the match PDA\n   242→- [ ] Worker builds and submits the `settle` instruction with the secret, all required accounts (match PDA, config, entropy, treasury, creator, opponent, profiles, platform program), and the server keypair as caller\n   243→- [ ] On successful settlement, worker updates the round's DB phase to `settled` and stores `settle_tx`, `result_hash`, `result_side`, `winner`\n   244→- [ ] On transient failure (tx dropped, blockhash expired, network error), worker retries up to 5 times with exponential backoff (base 2s, max 30s)\n   245→- [ ] On permanent failure (commitment mismatch, invalid phase, account not found), worker marks the round as failed and logs to `operator_events` without retrying\n   246→- [ ] Worker poll interval is configurable (default: 2 seconds)\n   247→- [ ] Worker logs each attempt to `operator_events` with type `settle_submitted`, `settle_confirmed`, `settle_failed`, or `settle_retried`\n   248→- [ ] If `resolve_deadline` has passed and settlement has not succeeded, worker logs a `timeout_detected` event (the on-chain timeout refund is triggered by any user, not by the backend)\n   249→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_013SMc3BMP8E6SA5d6gqSxGa","session_id":"c9591fb4-7b0c-48b9-bca6-a93e05209d51","uuid":"f6626f5d-8f49-4a7a-bd6d-376393342cb5"}
