{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01MMAaShqRwsoL5C3eQBh44R","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Implementation History — 006-fairness-backend\n     2→\n     3→Iteration log for the autonomous spec loop. Each entry records what was\n     4→attempted and whether it succeeded. The agent reads this file at the start\n     5→of every iteration to understand prior context.\n     6→\n     7→---\n     8→\n     9→## Iteration 1 — Scaffold `services/backend/` package\n    10→\n    11→**Item**: [infra] Scaffold `services/backend/` package\n    12→**Status**: Done\n    13→\n    14→Created:\n    15→- `services/backend/package.json` — `@rng-utopia/backend`, Hono + `@solana/web3.js` deps, ESM, tsx watch dev script\n    16→- `services/backend/tsconfig.json` — extends `@rng-utopia/config/tsconfig.node.json`, overrides rootDir/outDir\n    17→- `services/backend/eslint.config.js` — uses shared `nodeConfig`\n    18→- `services/backend/src/config.ts` — env config loader reading `DATABASE_URL`, `RPC_URL`, `SERVER_KEYPAIR` (JSON array keypair), `PORT` (default 3100)\n    19→- `services/backend/src/index.ts` — Hono HTTP server with placeholder `/health` endpoint, uses Hono's `export default { port, fetch }` pattern\n    20→\n    21→Verification:\n    22→- `pnpm install` — success (hono resolved as +1 new package)\n    23→- `pnpm --filter @rng-utopia/backend build` — success (tsc --noEmit, clean)\n    24→- `pnpm typecheck` — 18/18 packages pass\n    25→- `pnpm lint` — 18/18 packages pass (0 errors, existing warnings only)\n    26→- `pnpm --filter @rng-utopia/platform build` — success (no regression)\n    27→\n    28→Note: `pnpm build:all` has pre-existing failures in `chart-the-course`, `coinflip`, `slots-utopia`, `tug-of-earn` apps — unrelated to this change.\n    29→\n    30→## Iteration 1 — 2026-03-11T14:00:43Z — OK\n    31→- **Log**: iteration-001.log\n    32→\n    33→## Iteration 2 — Postgres migrations\n    34→\n    35→**Item**: [backend] Postgres migrations\n    36→**Status**: Done\n    37→\n    38→Created:\n    39→- `services/backend/migrations/001_init.sql` — `rounds` + `operator_events` tables with all columns, types, constraints, and 4 indexes (`rounds(phase)`, `rounds(creator)`, `operator_events(pda, created_at)`, `operator_events(event_type, created_at)`)\n    40→- `services/backend/src/migrate.ts` — Simple migration runner with `_migrations` version tracking table, idempotent (re-run skips applied), CLI with `status` subcommand\n    41→- Added `postgres` dependency (postgresjs v3) to `services/backend/package.json`\n    42→- Added `migrate` and `migrate:status` scripts to package.json\n    43→\n    44→Verification:\n    45→- `pnpm typecheck` — 18/18 packages pass\n    46→- `pnpm lint` — backend passes (0 errors)\n    47→- `pnpm migrate` — applied 001_init.sql successfully against local Postgres\n    48→- Re-ran `pnpm migrate` — idempotent (\"All migrations are up to date\")\n    49→- Verified all tables, columns, and indexes via `psql \\d` output\n    50→\n    51→## Iteration 2 — 2026-03-11T14:08:25Z — OK\n    52→- **Log**: iteration-002.log\n    53→\n    54→## Iteration 3 — DB client module\n    55→\n    56→**Item**: [backend] DB client module (`src/db.ts`)\n    57→**Status**: Done\n    58→\n    59→Created:\n    60→- `services/backend/src/db.ts` — DB client module with typed query functions using `postgres` (postgresjs) library\n    61→\n    62→Features:\n    63→- `createDb(databaseUrl)` factory returns a `Db` interface with connection pool\n    64→- `insertRound(params)` — inserts a new round (throws on duplicate PDA via primary key)\n    65→- `updateRoundPhase(pda, newPhase, updates?)` — transitions phase with unidirectional guard. Validates against `VALID_TRANSITIONS` state machine: `created→locked`, `created→expired`, `locked→settling`, `settling→settled`. Sets `updated_at = now()` on every phase change. Optional extra column updates (target_slot, settle_tx, result fields) via COALESCE.\n    66→- `getRoundByPda(pda)` — returns single round or undefined\n    67→- `getRoundsByPhase(phase)` — returns all rounds matching a phase\n    68→- `insertOperatorEvent(pda, eventType, payload?)` — appends to operator_events audit log\n    69→- `close()` — gracefully ends connection pool\n    70→- TypeScript types: `RoundPhase`, `OperatorEventType`, `Round`, `InsertRoundParams`, `OperatorEvent`, `Db`\n    71→- `secret` column is never logged (no console.log or error message references)\n    72→\n    73→Verification:\n    74→- `pnpm typecheck` — passes (0 errors)\n    75→- `pnpm lint` — passes (0 errors)\n    76→\n    77→## Iteration 3 — 2026-03-11T14:13:45Z — OK\n    78→- **Log**: iteration-003.log\n    79→\n    80→## Iteration 4 — Secret generation + commitment utilities\n    81→\n    82→**Item**: [backend] Secret generation + commitment utilities (`src/fairness.ts`)\n    83→**Status**: Done\n    84→\n    85→Created:\n    86→- `services/backend/src/fairness.ts` — Three exported functions:\n    87→  - `generateSecret()`: 32-byte CSPRNG via `crypto.randomBytes(32)`\n    88→  - `computeCommitment(secret)`: SHA256 hash matching `packages/fairness/src/commitment.ts` algorithm\n    89→  - `deriveMatchPda(creator, nonce)`: PDA derivation with seeds `[\"match\", creator, nonce.to_le_bytes()]` using coinflip program ID\n    90→- `services/backend/src/__tests__/fairness.test.ts` — 11 unit tests covering:\n    91→  - Secret: 32-byte length, uniqueness\n    92→  - Commitment: known SHA256 constant match, algorithm cross-check, determinism, different-input-different-output\n    93→  - PDA: return type, manual derivation match, bigint nonce support, different nonces/creators produce different PDAs\n    94→- `services/backend/vitest.config.ts` — vitest config (node environment)\n    95→\n    96→Verification:\n    97→- `npx tsc --noEmit` — pass (0 errors)\n    98→- `npx eslint .` — pass (0 errors)\n    99→- `npx vitest run` — 11 tests pass\n   100→\n   101→## Iteration 4 — 2026-03-11T14:18:52Z — OK\n   102→- **Log**: iteration-004.log\n   103→\n   104→## Iteration 5 — Partial transaction builder\n   105→\n   106→**Item**: [backend] Partial transaction builder (`src/tx-builder.ts`)\n   107→**Status**: Done\n   108→\n   109→Created:\n   110→- `services/backend/src/tx-builder.ts` — Builds `create_match` transactions without `@coral-xyz/anchor` dependency\n   111→\n   112→Features:\n   113→- `buildCreateMatchTx(params)` — async function that:\n   114→  - Derives match PDA via `deriveMatchPda(creator, nonce)` from fairness.ts\n   115→  - Derives config PDA with seeds `[\"coinflip_config\"]`\n   116→  - Manually encodes Borsh instruction data: discriminator(8) + commitment(32) + tier(1) + side(1) + nonce(8) = 50 bytes\n   117→  - Assembles `TransactionInstruction` with accounts in IDL order: creator (signer+writable), server (signer), coinflip_match (writable), config, system_program\n   118→  - Sets creator wallet as fee payer (server pays zero on-chain cost)\n   119→  - Fetches recent blockhash at build time via `connection.getLatestBlockhash()`\n   120→  - Partially signs with server keypair only\n   121→  - Serializes with `requireAllSignatures: false` and returns base64 string + matchPda\n   122→- Exported `COINFLIP_PROGRAM_ID` from fairness.ts (was module-private, needed by tx-builder)\n   123→- Uses only `@solana/web3.js` (no new dependencies)\n   124→\n   125→Verification:\n   126→- `tsc --noEmit` — pass (0 errors)\n   127→- `eslint .` — pass (0 errors)\n   128→- `vitest run` — 11 existing tests still pass\n   129→\n   130→## Iteration 5 — 2026-03-11T14:24:21Z — OK\n   131→- **Log**: iteration-005.log\n   132→\n   133→## Iteration 6 — POST /fairness/coinflip/create endpoint\n   134→\n   135→**Item**: [backend] `POST /fairness/coinflip/create` endpoint handler\n   136→**Status**: Done\n   137→\n   138→Created:\n   139→- `services/backend/src/routes/create.ts` — Hono route handler with `createCoinflipRoutes(deps)` factory\n   140→  - Valida