/backend/src/config.ts` — Added `authClockSkewSeconds` config field (reads `AUTH_CLOCK_SKEW_SECONDS` env, default 60)\n   177→- `services/backend/src/index.ts` — Wired auth middleware on `/fairness/*` routes\n   178→- `services/backend/package.json` — Added `tweetnacl` (^1.0.3) and `bs58` (^6.0.0) dependencies\n   179→\n   180→Verification:\n   181→- `tsc --noEmit` — pass (0 errors)\n   182→- `eslint .` — pass (0 errors)\n   183→- `pnpm typecheck` — 18/18 packages pass\n   184→- `pnpm lint` — 18/18 packages pass\n   185→- `vitest run` — 11 existing tests pass\n   186→\n   187→## Iteration 7 — 2026-03-11T14:36:48Z — OK\n   188→- **Log**: iteration-007.log\n   189→\n   190→## Iteration 8 — Rate limiting middleware\n   191→\n   192→**Item**: [backend] Rate limiting middleware (`src/middleware/rate-limit.ts`)\n   193→**Status**: Done\n   194→\n   195→Created:\n   196→- `services/backend/src/middleware/rate-limit.ts` — In-memory sliding-window rate limiter\n   197→  - `createRateLimitMiddleware(config)` factory returns Hono middleware\n   198→  - Skips non-POST requests (GET endpoints not rate-limited)\n   199→  - Per-wallet limit keyed by `wallet` field from JSON body (default 10/min via `RATE_LIMIT_PER_WALLET`)\n   200→  - Global limit for all POST requests combined (default 100/min via `RATE_LIMIT_GLOBAL`)\n   201→  - Returns 429 with `Retry-After` header when either limit exceeded\n   202→  - Sliding window: prunes expired timestamps on each check\n   203→  - Counters reset on service restart (in-memory, no Redis)\n   204→\n   205→Updated:\n   206→- `services/backend/src/config.ts` — Added `rateLimitPerWallet` and `rateLimitGlobal` config fields\n   207→- `services/backend/src/index.ts` — Wired rate limit middleware on `/fairness/*` routes (before auth middleware)\n   208→\n   209→Verification:\n   210→- `tsc --noEmit` — pass (0 errors)\n   211→- `eslint .` — pass (0 errors)\n   212→- `vitest run` — 11 existing tests pass\n   213→- `pnpm typecheck` — passes\n   214→- `pnpm lint` — passes\n   215→\n   216→## Iteration 8 — 2026-03-11T14:42:00Z — OK\n   217→- **Log**: iteration-008.log\n   218→\n   219→## Iteration 8 — 2026-03-11T14:38:45Z — OK\n   220→- **Log**: iteration-008.log\n   221→\n   222→## Iteration 9 — Settlement worker poll loop\n   223→\n   224→**Item**: [backend] Settlement worker poll loop (`src/worker/settlement.ts`)\n   225→**Status**: Done\n   226→\n   227→Created:\n   228→- `services/backend/src/worker/settlement.ts` — Settlement worker that polls chain for locked matches\n   229→  - `createSettlementWorker(deps)` factory returns a `SettlementWorker` with `start()`, `stop()`, `isRunning`, `poll()`\n   230→  - Polls via `getProgramAccounts` with memcmp filters: dataSize=246, phase byte at offset 114 = PHASE_LOCKED (1), server pubkey at offset 72 matches service keypair\n   231→  - Parses target_slot (u64 LE at offset 148) from account data\n   232→  - Tracks discovered PDAs in-memory to log `match_detected` only once per match\n   233→  - Transitions DB phase from `created` → `locked` when match first detected on-chain\n   234→  - Calls optional `onSettleReady` callback when target_slot is reached (hook for settle-tx module)\n   235→  - Configurable poll interval (default 2s via `WORKER_POLL_INTERVAL_MS` env var)\n   236→  - Error-resilient: logs errors but doesn't crash the loop\n   237→\n   238→Updated:\n   239→- `services/backend/src/config.ts` — Added `workerPollIntervalMs` config field (reads `WORKER_POLL_INTERVAL_MS`, default 2000)\n   240→- `services/backend/src/index.ts` — Imports and starts settlement worker on service boot\n   241→\n   242→Verification:\n   243→- `tsc --noEmit` — pass (0 errors)\n   244→- `eslint .` — pass (0 errors)\n   245→- `vitest run` — 11 existing tests pass\n   246→\n   247→## Iteration 9 — 2026-03-11T14:46:02Z — OK\n   248→- **Log**: iteration-009.log\n   249→\n   250→## Iteration 10 — Settle transaction builder + submission\n   251→\n   252→**Item**: [backend] Settle transaction builder + submission (`src/worker/settle-tx.ts`)\n   253→**Status**: Done\n   254→\n   255→Created:\n   256→- `services/backend/src/worker/settle-tx.ts` — Settle transaction builder and submitter\n   257→  - `settleMatch(deps, pda)` — async function that orchestrates the full settle flow:\n   258→    1. Retrieves secret from DB `rounds` table by PDA\n   259→    2. Fetches match account data from chain (creator, opponent, creator_side, algorithm_ver)\n   260→    3. Fetches config PDA to resolve treasury address\n   261→    4. Reads first 32 bytes of entropy account\n   262→    5. Pre-computes result: `SHA256(secret || entropy || pda_bytes || algo_ver)`, `result_side = hash[0] % 2`\n   263→    6. Derives player profile PDAs (`[\"player_profile\", wallet]` on platform program)\n   264→    7. Builds settle instruction with all 11 accounts in IDL order (caller, match, config, entropy, treasury, creator, opponent, creator_profile, opponent_profile, platform_program, system_program)\n   265→    8. Encodes instruction data: discriminator(8) + secret(32) = 40 bytes\n   266→    9. Signs with server keypair as caller/fee payer\n   267→    10. Submits via `sendRawTransaction` + `confirmTransaction`\n   268→    11. Updates DB: phase `settling` → `settled`, stores settle_tx, result_hash, result_side, winner\n   269→    12. Logs `settle_submitted` + `settle_confirmed` operator events\n   270→  - `PermanentSettleError` — for non-retryable failures (round not found, wrong phase, account missing)\n   271→  - `TransientSettleError` — for retryable failures (entropy not available)\n   272→\n   273→Updated:\n   274→- `services/backend/src/config.ts` — Added `entropyAccount` config field (reads `ENTROPY_ACCOUNT` env, defaults to SlotHashes sysvar)\n   275→- `services/backend/src/index.ts` — Wired `onSettleReady` callback on settlement worker that calls `settleMatch()`, with structured JSON logging for success/error\n   276→\n   277→Verification:\n   278→- `tsc --noEmit` — pass (0 errors)\n   279→- `eslint .` — pass (0 errors)\n   280→- `vitest run` — 11 existing tests pass\n   281→\n   282→## Iteration 10 — 2026-03-11T14:52:00Z — OK\n   283→- **Log**: iteration-010.log\n   284→\n   285→## Iteration 10 — 2026-03-11T14:51:52Z — OK\n   286→- **Log**: iteration-010.log\n   287→\n   288→## Iteration 11 — Settlement retry logic\n   289→\n   290→**Item**: [backend] Settlement retry logic (`src/worker/retry.ts`)\n   291→**Status**: Done\n   292→\n   293→Created:\n   294→- `services/backend/src/worker/retry.ts` — Retry-aware settlement wrapper with `createRetrySettler(deps)` factory\n   295→  - `attemptSettle(pda)` — safe to call repeatedly from poll loop, handles all retry scheduling\n   296→  - In-memory per-PDA retry tracking: attempts count, next retry timestamp\n   297→  - Exponential backoff: base 2s, doubling each retry, capped at 30s (delays: 2s, 4s, 8s, 16s, 30s)\n   298→  - Max 5 retries — after which logs `settle_failed` with \"max retries exceeded\"\n   299→  - `PermanentSettleError` detection: immediately marks failed, logs `settle_failed`, no retry\n   300→  - All other errors (TransientSettleError, network errors, tx failures) treated as transient → retried\n   301→  - `resolve_deadline` check before each attempt: reads CoinflipMatch account offset 156 (i64 LE), compares to current unix time. If deadline passed, logs `timeout_detected`, stops retrying\n   302→  - Structured JSON logging for all outcomes (success, permanent failure, transient retry, timeout)\n   303→\n   304→Updated:\n   305→- `services/backend/src/index.ts` — Replaced direct `settleMatch` call with `createRetrySettler` wrapper. Worker's `onSettleReady` now delegates to `retrySettler.attemptSettle(pda)` which handles retry logic transparently\n   306→\n   307→Verification:\n   308→- `tsc --noEmit` — pass (0 errors)\n   309→- `eslint .` — pass (0 errors)\n   310→- `vitest run` — 11 existing tests pass\n   311→- `pnpm typecheck` — 18/18 packages pass\n   312→- `pnpm lint` — 1