{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_013SMc3BMP8E6SA5d6gqSxGa","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now I have all the information I need. Let me create the comprehensive inventory report:\n\n---\n\n## Inventory Report: Spec 006-Fairness-Backend On-Chain Assets\n\n### 1. Coinflip Program Instructions\n\n**Location**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/solana/programs/coinflip/src/instructions/`\n\nAll instruction handlers follow the pattern: `pub fn handler(ctx: Context<Accounts>, args...)`.\n\n| Instruction | File | Handler Line | Accounts Struct | Handler Line | Purpose |\n|-------------|------|--------|-------|---------|---------|\n| `create_match` | `create_match.rs` | 41 | `CreateMatch<'info>` | 41 | Player creates match with server co-signing; stores commitment |\n| `join_match` | `join_match.rs` | 34 | `JoinMatch<'info>` | 34 | Opponent joins; locks match, sets target_slot + resolve_deadline |\n| `settle` | `settle.rs` | 65 | `Settle<'info>` | 65 | Permissionless; reveals secret, derives result, pays winner (core fairness) |\n| `request_refund` | `request_refund.rs` | 32 | `RequestRefund<'info>` | 32 | Either player votes for mutual refund; auto-executes on both votes |\n| `timeout_refund` | `timeout_refund.rs` | 33 | `TimeoutRefund<'info>` | 33 | Permissionless; refunds both players if deadline passes unsigned |\n| `cancel_match` | `cancel_match.rs` | 24 | `CancelMatch<'info>` | 24 | Creator-only; closes match in WAITING phase (refunds full escrow) |\n| `initialize_config` | `initialize_config.rs` | 24 | `InitializeConfig<'info>` | 24 | Admin-only; creates global config PDA (treasury, pause flag) |\n\n**Key Detail**: Settlement (`settle`) is **permissionless** — anyone with the secret can submit the settlement transaction. The server pays zero on-chain cost (creator is fee payer on `create_match`).\n\n---\n\n### 2. Coinflip State Accounts\n\n**Location**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/solana/programs/coinflip/src/state.rs`\n\n#### CoinflipConfig (Singleton PDA)\n- **Seeds**: `[\"coinflip_config\"]`\n- **Lines**: 5-16\n- **Fields**:\n  - `authority: Pubkey` — admin who updates config\n  - `treasury: Pubkey` — fee destination wallet\n  - `paused: bool` — pause flag (rejects new matches)\n  - `bump: u8` — PDA bump seed\n\n#### CoinflipMatch (Per-Match PDA)\n- **Seeds**: `[\"match\", creator.key(), nonce.to_le_bytes()]`\n- **Lines**: 20-61\n- **Account Size**: 246 bytes (8 discriminator + 238 InitSpace)\n- **Key Fields**:\n  - `creator: Pubkey` — match creator\n  - `opponent: Pubkey` — joiner (Pubkey::default() if empty)\n  - `server: Pubkey` — server key that co-signed create + settles\n  - `tier: u8` — tier index (0-7)\n  - `entry_amount: u64` — entry in lamports (from tier)\n  - `creator_side: u8` — 0=Heads, 1=Tails\n  - `phase: u8` — match lifecycle (0=WAITING, 1=LOCKED, 2=SETTLED, 3=REFUNDED)\n  - **Fairness Core**:\n    - `commitment: [u8; 32]` — SHA256(server_secret), stored at create time\n    - `algorithm_ver: u8` — which algorithm for result derivation\n    - `target_slot: u64` — entropy slot (set on join, used by settle)\n    - `result_hash: [u8; 32]` — derived result (set on settle)\n    - `result: u8` — winning side (0 or 1, valid when settled)\n  - `winner: Pubkey` — winner's address (after settlement)\n  - `created_at: i64` — unix timestamp\n  - `nonce: u64` — match creation nonce (from player profile)\n  - `bump: u8` — PDA bump\n  - Refund voting: `creator_wants_refund`, `opponent_wants_refund` (bool)\n  - Timeout: `resolve_deadline: i64` — unix timestamp deadline\n\n#### Event: MatchSettled\n- **Lines**: 70-82\n- **Emitted on**: `settle` instruction success\n- **Fields**:\n  - `creator, opponent, winner: Pubkey`\n  - `commitment: [u8; 32]` — original commitment\n  - `secret: [u8; 32]` — revealed secret (for verification)\n  - `entropy: [u8; 32]` — entropy from SlotHashes\n  - `result_hash: [u8; 32]` — SHA256(secret || entropy || pda || algo_ver)\n  - `result_side: u8` — winning side (0 or 1)\n  - `payout_amount: u64` — winner's net payout (after fees)\n  - `fee_amount: u64` — platform fee (3% of pool)\n\n#### Phase Constants\n- **Lines**: 64-67\n- `PHASE_WAITING = 0` → accepting joiner\n- `PHASE_LOCKED = 1` → both players in, awaiting entropy (target_slot)\n- `PHASE_SETTLED = 2` → result determined, payout distributed\n- `PHASE_REFUNDED = 3` → mutual refund executed or timeout triggered\n\n---\n\n### 3. Shared Fairness Module\n\n**Location**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/solana/shared/src/fairness.rs`\n\n#### Constants\n- **Line 5**: `ALGORITHM_VERSION: u8 = 1` — current fairness algorithm\n- **Line 8**: `ENTROPY_SLOT_OFFSET: u64 = 12` — slots to wait after join before entropy is trustworthy\n\n#### Core Fairness Functions\n\n| Function | Lines | Signature | Purpose |\n|----------|-------|-----------|---------|\n| `verify_commitment` | 11-18 | `(commitment: &[u8; 32], secret: &[u8; 32]) → Result<()>` | Checks SHA256(secret) == commitment |\n| `derive_result` | 21-28 | `(secret, entropy, game_pda, algo_ver) → [u8; 32]` | Derives result hash: SHA256(secret \\|\\| entropy \\|\\| pda \\|\\| algo_ver) |\n| `read_mock_entropy` | 31-37 | `(account: &AccountInfo) → Result<[u8; 32]>` | Reads first 32 bytes of entropy account |\n\n#### Errors\n- **Lines**: 39-45\n- `CommitmentMismatch` — SHA256(secret) ≠ stored commitment\n- `EntropyTooShort` — account data < 32 bytes\n\n#### Tests (lines 47-85)\n- Commitment verification: valid/invalid secrets\n- Result determinism: same inputs → same hash\n- Result sensitivity: different algo_ver → different hash\n\n**Key Pattern**: `result_side = result_hash[0] % 2` — first byte mod 2 determines Heads(0) or Tails(1).\n\n---\n\n### 4. Shared Fees Module\n\n**Location**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/solana/shared/src/fees.rs`\n\n#### Constants (lines 1-11)\n| Constant | Value | Notes |\n|----------|-------|-------|\n| `MAX_FEE_BPS` | 1000 | safety cap: 10% max (compile-time assertion) |\n| `TOTAL_FEE_BPS` | 300 | total platform fee (3%) |\n| `REVENUE_BPS` | 200 | 200 bps → platform revenue |\n| `RAKEBACK_BPS` | 70 | 70 bps → rakeback pool |\n| `CHEST_BPS` | 30 | 30 bps → chest treasury |\n\n#### Functions\n\n| Function | Lines | Signature | Purpose |\n|----------|-------|-----------|---------|\n| `calculate_fee` | 18-20 | `(amount: u64) → u64` | Returns fee in lamports; `(amount × 300 / 10_000)` |\n| `calculate_net_payout` | 25-28 | `(pool: u64) → (u64, u64)` | Returns `(fee, net_payout)` where `net = pool - fee` |\n| `split_fee` | 31-36 | `(fee: u64) → (u64, u64, u64)` | Returns `(revenue, rakeback, chest)` by pro-rata split |\n\n**Usage in Settle**: Pool = `entry_amount × 2` (both players' stakes). Fee is deducted; winner takes all remaining (net_payout + any rent surplus).\n\n---\n\n### 5. Fairness Package (TypeScript)\n\n**Location**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/packages/fairness/src/commitment.ts`\n\n#### Functions\n| Function | Lines | Signature | Purpose |\n|----------|-------|-----------|---------|\n| `computeCommitment` | 8-12 | `(serverSeed: string) → string` | SHA256(hex→bytes) returning hex string |\n| `verifyCommitment` | 17-20 | `(serverSeed, commitment: string) → boolean` | Case-insensitive hex comparison |\n\n**Note**: These functions **mirror** the on-chain Rust fairness.rs module and are **reused by the backend service** for client-side and server-side verification.\n\n---\n\n### 6. Anchor Client IDL\n\n**Location**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/packages/anchor-client/src/coinflip.json`\n\n**Program ID**: `BdHFeqmkYe7znXV1Avk3zz496Pjo8QhEDN4MKPUTAWwx`\n\n**IDL Coverage**: Defines instruction discriminators, accounts, and argument schemas for:\n- `create_match` (lines 68+)\n- `cancel_match` (lines 10-66)\n- `join_match`\n- `settle`\n- `request_refund`\n- `timeout_refund`\n- `initialize_config`\n\n**Key Detail**: `create_match` accounts in IDL order:\n1. `creator` (signer, writable, fee payer)\n2. `server` (signer, co-sign authority)\n3. `coinflip_match` (writable, PDA)\n4. `config` (readonly, PDA)\n5. `system_program`\n\n---\n\n### 7. Errors (Coinflip Program)\n\n**Location**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/solana/programs/coinflip/src/error.rs`\n\n**Base Offset**: 6000 (Anchor adds this to all error codes)\n\n| Error Code | Rust Name | Message | Line |\n|------------|-----------|---------|------|\n| 6100 | `InvalidSide` | Invalid side: must be 0 or 1 | 7 |\n| 6101 | `InvalidTier` | Invalid tier index | 11 |\n| 6102 | `InvalidPhase` | Match is not in expected phase | 15 |\n| 6103 | `InsufficientFunds` | Insufficient funds for entry | 19 |\n| 6104 | `CannotJoinOwnMatch` | Creator cannot join their own match | 23 |\n| 6105 | `ServerMismatch` | Server key mismatch | 27 |\n| 6106 | `CommitmentMismatch` | Commitment ≠ SHA256(secret) | 31 |\n| 6107 | `CannotCancel` | Only WAITING phase cancellable | 35 |\n| 6108 | `LockTimeoutNotElapsed` | Timeout not elapsed | 39 |\n| 6109 | `EntropyTooShort` | Entropy < 32 bytes | 43 |\n| 6110 | `DeadlineNotReached` | Resolve deadline not reached | 47 |\n| 6111 | `AccountMismatch` | Account key ≠ expected value | 51 |\n| 6112 | `NotParticipant` | Caller not a participant | 55 |\n| 6113 | `AlreadyVotedRefund` | Caller already voted | 59 |\n\n---\n\n### 8. Backend Service Implementation Status\n\n**Location**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/`\n\n**Status**: COMPLETE (20 iterations + devnet E2E tested)\n\n#### Modules Implemented\n\n| Module | File | Purpose |\n|--------|------|---------|\n| **Config** | `src/config.ts` | Env loader: RPC_URL, DATABASE_URL, SERVER_KEYPAIR, PORT, auth skew, rate limits, worker poll interval |\n| **DB Client** | `src/db.ts` | Postgres wrapper with `rounds` + `operator_events` tables; phase transitions, operator audit trail |\n| **Fairness Utilities** | `src/fairness.ts` | `generateSecret()`, `computeCommitment()`, `deriveMatchPda()` |\n| **TX Builder** | `src/tx-builder.ts` | `buildCreateMatchTx()` — builds + partial-signs create_match with Borsh encoding (no Anchor dep) |\n| **Routes: Create** | `src/routes/create.ts` | `POST /fairness/coinflip/create` — generates secret, builds tx, stores round, returns partial tx + PDA |\n| **Routes: Rounds** | `src/routes/rounds.ts` | `GET /fairness/rounds/:pda` — serves round data, redacts secret for unsettled, includes verification payloads |\n| **Routes: Health** | `src/routes/health.ts` | `GET /health` — status, version, balance, DB connectivity, worker state, unsettled stats |\n| **Auth Middleware** | `src/middleware/auth.ts` | Ed25519 wallet signature verification, timestamp replay protection (60s skew) |\n| **Rate Limit Middleware** | `src/middleware/rate-limit.ts` | Per-wallet (10/min) + global (100/min) sliding-window limits; returns 429 with Retry-After |\n| **Settlement Worker** | `src/worker/settlement.ts` | Polls chain via `getProgramAccounts` (memcmp filters); detects PHASE_LOCKED matches, triggers settle |\n| **Settle TX Builder** | `src/worker/settle-tx.ts` | Builds settle instruction: reads entropy, derives result, calls update_player_profile_cpi, submits tx |\n| **Retry Logic** | `src/worker/retry.ts` | Exponential backoff (2s→4s→8s→16s→30s, 5 max attempts); permanent vs transient error classification |\n| **Logger** | `src/logger.ts` | Structured JSON logging (no secrets ever logged) |\n| **Migrations** | `src/migrate.ts` | Idempotent Postgres migration runner |\n| **Main** | `src/index.ts` | Hono server entry; wires all routes, middleware, worker |\n\n#### Database Schema\n\n**`rounds` table** (23 columns):\n- `pda` (PRIMARY KEY)\n- `game`, `creator`, `server_key`, `tier`, `side`, `nonce`, phase\n- Fairness fields: `secret` (BYTEA), `commitment`, `algorithm_version`\n- Settlement fields: `target_slot`, `settle_tx`, `result_hash`, `result_side`, `winner`\n- Metadata: `settle_attempts`, `created_at`, `updated_at`\n\n**`operator_events` table** (audit trail):\n- `id` (BIGSERIAL PRIMARY KEY)\n- `pda` (nullable)\n- `event_type` (enum: secret_generated, match_detected, settle_submitted, settle_confirmed, settle_failed, timeout_detected, etc.)\n- `payload` (JSONB)\n- `created_at`\n\n**Indexes**: `rounds(phase)`, `rounds(creator)`, `operator_events(pda, created_at)`, `operator_events(event_type, created_at)`\n\n#### Test Coverage\n- **Unit tests** (26 tests): fairness utilities, auth, rate limiting\n- **Integration tests** (4 tests): full create → join → settle lifecycle with mock connection\n- **Endpoint tests** (9 tests): HTTP layer (auth, rate limit, 404, 409, 429 responses)\n- **Total**: 39 tests, all passing\n\n---\n\n## Gap Analysis Summary\n\n### On-Chain Alignment\n- ✓ **Commitment storage**: CoinflipMatch.commitment (32 bytes, set at create_match line 77)\n- ✓ **Algorithm version**: CoinflipMatch.algorithm_ver (set to ALGORITHM_VERSION=1 at line 78)\n- ✓ **Entropy source**: SlotHashes sysvar (ENTROPY_SLOT_OFFSET=12 slots after join, line 60 join_match.rs)\n- ✓ **Target slot**: CoinflipMatch.target_slot (set on join_match line 60)\n- ✓ **Settlement permissionless**: settle instruction has no server signer constraint (anyone can call with secret)\n- ✓ **Result derivation**: derive_result() matches settle's formula (line 92 settle.rs)\n- ✓ **Fairness event**: MatchSettled emitted with all verification data (lines 109-120 settle.rs)\n\n### Backend Implementation Alignment\n- ✓ **Secret generation**: crypto.randomBytes(32) CSPRNG\n- ✓ **Commitment computation**: SHA256(secret) matching packages/fairness\n- ✓ **PDA derivation**: [\"match\", creator, nonce.to_le_bytes()] seeds match on-chain\n- ✓ **Partial signing**: Server co-signs create_match, user is fee payer\n- ✓ **Settlement worker**: Polls getProgramAccounts with phase + server memcmp filters\n- ✓ **Entropy handling**: Reads 32 bytes from SlotHashes sysvar\n- ✓ **Result verification**: Pre-computes result_hash via derive_result before settle\n- ✓ **Retry logic**: Exponential backoff with permanent/transient classification\n- ✓ **Database audit trail**: operator_events logs all state transitions\n- ✓ **Public verification endpoint**: GET /fairness/rounds/:pda serves secrets post-settlement\n\n### Acceptance Criteria Coverage\nAll 7 Functional Requirements (FR-1 through FR-7) marked complete in implementation history:\n1. ✓ FR-1: Secret generation + transaction signing\n2. ✓ FR-2: Settlement worker with retry logic\n3. ✓ FR-3: Round state storage + operator events\n4. ✓ FR-4: Round verification endpoint\n5. ✓ FR-5: Request authentication (wallet signature + timestamp)\n6. ✓ FR-6: Health & observability endpoints\n7. ✓ FR-7: Rate limiting (per-wallet + global)\n\n---\n\n## Files Summary by Type\n\n### On-Chain (Rust)\n- **Instructions**: 7 handlers across 7 files (create_match, join_match, settle, request_refund, timeout_refund, cancel_match, initialize_config)\n- **State**: CoinflipMatch (246 bytes), CoinflipConfig, MatchSettled event\n- **Fairness**: verify_commitment, derive_result, read_mock_entropy (+ error types)\n- **Fees**: calculate_net_payout (3% split: 200 rev / 70 rakeback / 30 chest)\n\n### Off-Chain (TypeScript Backend)\n- **Core**: 14 source files (config, db, fairness, tx-builder, 3 routes, 2 middleware, 3 worker modules, logger, migrate)\n- **Tests**: 4 test files (fairness, auth, rate-limit, integration, endpoints = 39 tests total)\n- **Database**: 2 tables, 4 indexes, migrations versioning\n\n### Frontend/Shared (TypeScript)\n- **Fairness Package**: 2 functions (computeCommitment, verifyCommitment) mirrored on-chain\n- **Anchor Client IDL**: Full instruction definitions for all 7 instructions\n\n---\n\nThis inventory is complete and ready for the gap analysis phase of spec 006-fairness-backend."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a2904a00881d7c5cb (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 72436\ntool_uses: 30\nduration_ms: 90481</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c9591fb4-7b0c-48b9-bca6-a93e05209d51","uuid":"09fe3bae-c8fe-4c25-a795-4ea2a193dcb2","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Inventory the on-chain coinflip program and shared crate for spec 006-fairness-backend gap analysis.\n\nCheck these areas in `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/`:\n\n1. **Coinflip program instructions**: `solana/programs/coinflip/src/instructions/` — list all `pub fn` with file:line\n2. **Coinflip state**: `solana/programs/coinflip/src/state.rs` — CoinflipMatch fields, phases\n3. **Shared fairness**: `solana/shared/src/fairness.rs` — verify_commitment, derive_result, ALGORITHM_VERSION\n4. **Shared fees**: `solana/shared/src/fees.rs` — calculate_net_payout\n5. **Fairness package**: `packages/fairness/src/commitment.ts` — computeCommitment, verifyCommitment\n6. **Anchor client IDL**: `packages/anchor-client/src/coinflip.json` — check create_match and settle instruction definitions\n\nRead the actual files and report file paths + line numbers for key definitions.","agentId":"a2904a00881d7c5cb","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now I have all the information I need. Let me create the comprehensive inventory report:\n\n---\n\n## Inventory Report: Spec 006-Fairness-Backend On-Chain Assets\n\n### 1. Coinflip Program Instructions\n\n**Location**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/solana/programs/coinflip/src/instructions/`\n\nAll instruction handlers follow the pattern: `pub fn handler(ctx: Context<Accounts>, args...)`.\n\n| Instruction | File | Handler Line | Accounts Struct | Handler Line | Purpose |\n|-------------|------|--------|-------|---------|---------|\n| `create_match` | `create_match.rs` | 41 | `CreateMatch<'info>` | 41 | Player creates match with server co-signing; stores commitment |\n| `join_match` | `join_match.rs` | 34 | `JoinMatch<'info>` | 34 | Opponent joins; locks match, sets target_slot + resolve_deadline |\n| `settle` | `settle.rs` | 65 | `Settle<'info>` | 65 | Permissionless; reveals secret, derives result, pays winner (core fairness) |\n| `request_refund` | `request_refund.rs` | 32 | `RequestRefund<'info>` | 32 | Either player votes for mutual refund; auto-executes on both votes |\n| `timeout_refund` | `timeout_refund.rs` | 33 | `TimeoutRefund<'info>` | 33 | Permissionless; refunds both players if deadline passes unsigned |\n| `cancel_match` | `cancel_match.rs` | 24 | `CancelMatch<'info>` | 24 | Creator-only; closes match in WAITING phase (refunds full escrow) |\n| `initialize_config` | `initialize_config.rs` | 24 | `InitializeConfig<'info>` | 24 | Admin-only; creates global config PDA (treasury, pause flag) |\n\n**Key Detail**: Settlement (`settle`) is **permissionless** — anyone with the secret can submit the settlement transaction. The server pays zero on-chain cost (creator is fee payer on `create_match`).\n\n---\n\n### 2. Coinflip State Accounts\n\n**Location**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/solana/programs/coinflip/src/state.rs`\n\n#### CoinflipConfig (Singleton PDA)\n- **Seeds**: `[\"coinflip_config\"]`\n- **Lines**: 5-16\n- **Fields**:\n  - `authority: Pubkey` — admin who updates config\n  - `treasury: Pubkey` — fee destination wallet\n  - `paused: bool` — pause flag (rejects new matches)\n  - `bump: u8` — PDA bump seed\n\n#### CoinflipMatch (Per-Match PDA)\n- **Seeds**: `[\"match\", creator.key(), nonce.to_le_bytes()]`\n- **Lines**: 20-61\n- **Account Size**: 246 bytes (8 discriminator + 238 InitSpace)\n- **Key Fields**:\n  - `creator: Pubkey` — match creator\n  - `opponent: Pubkey` — joiner (Pubkey::default() if empty)\n  - `server: Pubkey` — server key that co-signed create + settles\n  - `tier: u8` — tier index (0-7)\n  - `entry_amount: u64` — entry in lamports (from tier)\n  - `creator_side: u8` — 0=Heads, 1=Tails\n  - `phase: u8` — match lifecycle (0=WAITING, 1=LOCKED, 2=SETTLED, 3=REFUNDED)\n  - **Fairness Core**:\n    - `commitment: [u8; 32]` — SHA256(server_secret), stored at create time\n    - `algorithm_ver: u8` — which algorithm for result derivation\n    - `target_slot: u64` — entropy slot (set on join, used by settle)\n    - `result_hash: [u8; 32]` — derived result (set on settle)\n    - `result: u8` — winning side (0 or 1, valid when settled)\n  - `winner: Pubkey` — winner's address (after settlement)\n  - `created_at: i64` — unix timestamp\n  - `nonce: u64` — match creation nonce (from player profile)\n  - `bump: u8` — PDA bump\n  - Refund voting: `creator_wants_refund`, `opponent_wants_refund` (bool)\n  - Timeout: `resolve_deadline: i64` — unix timestamp deadline\n\n#### Event: MatchSettled\n- **Lines**: 70-82\n- **Emitted on**: `settle` instruction success\n- **Fields**:\n  - `creator, opponent, winner: Pubkey`\n  - `commitment: [u8; 32]` — original commitment\n  - `secret: [u8; 32]` — revealed secret (for verification)\n  - `entropy: [u8; 32]` — entropy from SlotHashes\n  - `result_hash: [u8; 32]` — SHA256(secret || entropy || pda || algo_ver)\n  - `result_side: u8` — winning side (0 or 1)\n  - `payout_amount: u64` — winner's net payout (after fees)\n  - `fee_amount: u64` — platform fee (3% of pool)\n\n#### Phase Constants\n- **Lines**: 64-67\n- `PHASE_WAITING = 0` → accepting joiner\n- `PHASE_LOCKED = 1` → both players in, awaiting entropy (target_slot)\n- `PHASE_SETTLED = 2` → result determined, payout distributed\n- `PHASE_REFUNDED = 3` → mutual refund executed or timeout triggered\n\n---\n\n### 3. Shared Fairness Module\n\n**Location**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/solana/shared/src/fairness.rs`\n\n#### Constants\n- **Line 5**: `ALGORITHM_VERSION: u8 = 1` — current fairness algorithm\n- **Line 8**: `ENTROPY_SLOT_OFFSET: u64 = 12` — slots to wait after join before entropy is trustworthy\n\n#### Core Fairness Functions\n\n| Function | Lines | Signature | Purpose |\n|----------|-------|-----------|---------|\n| `verify_commitment` | 11-18 | `(commitment: &[u8; 32], secret: &[u8; 32]) → Result<()>` | Checks SHA256(secret) == commitment |\n| `derive_result` | 21-28 | `(secret, entropy, game_pda, algo_ver) → [u8; 32]` | Derives result hash: SHA256(secret \\|\\| entropy \\|\\| pda \\|\\| algo_ver) |\n| `read_mock_entropy` | 31-37 | `(account: &AccountInfo) → Result<[u8; 32]>` | Reads first 32 bytes of entropy account |\n\n#### Errors\n- **Lines**: 39-45\n- `CommitmentMismatch` — SHA256(secret) ≠ stored commitment\n- `EntropyTooShort` — account data < 32 bytes\n\n#### Tests (lines 47-85)\n- Commitment verification: valid/invalid secrets\n- Result determinism: same inputs → same hash\n- Result sensitivity: different algo_ver → different hash\n\n**Key Pattern**: `result_side = result_hash[0] % 2` — first byte mod 2 determines Heads(0) or Tails(1).\n\n---\n\n### 4. Shared Fees Module\n\n**Location**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/solana/shared/src/fees.rs`\n\n#### Constants (lines 1-11)\n| Constant | Value | Notes |\n|----------|-------|-------|\n| `MAX_FEE_BPS` | 1000 | safety cap: 10% max (compile-time assertion) |\n| `TOTAL_FEE_BPS` | 300 | total platform fee (3%) |\n| `REVENUE_BPS` | 200 | 200 bps → platform revenue |\n| `RAKEBACK_BPS` | 70 | 70 bps → rakeback pool |\n| `CHEST_BPS` | 30 | 30 bps → chest treasury |\n\n#### Functions\n\n| Function | Lines | Signature | Purpose |\n|----------|-------|-----------|---------|\n| `calculate_fee` | 18-20 | `(amount: u64) → u64` | Returns fee in lamports; `(amount × 300 / 10_000)` |\n| `calculate_net_payout` | 25-28 | `(pool: u64) → (u64, u64)` | Returns `(fee, net_payout)` where `net = pool - fee` |\n| `split_fee` | 31-36 | `(fee: u64) → (u64, u64, u64)` | Returns `(revenue, rakeback, chest)` by pro-rata split |\n\n**Usage in Settle**: Pool = `entry_amount × 2` (both players' stakes). Fee is deducted; winner takes all remaining (net_payout + any rent surplus).\n\n---\n\n### 5. Fairness Package (TypeScript)\n\n**Location**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/packages/fairness/src/commitment.ts`\n\n#### Functions\n| Function | Lines | Signature | Purpose |\n|----------|-------|-----------|---------|\n| `computeCommitment` | 8-12 | `(serverSeed: string) → string` | SHA256(hex→bytes) returning hex string |\n| `verifyCommitment` | 17-20 | `(serverSeed, commitment: string) → boolean` | Case-insensitive hex comparison |\n\n**Note**: These functions **mirror** the on-chain Rust fairness.rs module and are **reused by the backend service** for client-side and server-side verification.\n\n---\n\n### 6. Anchor Client IDL\n\n**Location**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/packages/anchor-client/src/coinflip.json`\n\n**Program ID**: `BdHFeqmkYe7znXV1Avk3zz496Pjo8QhEDN4MKPUTAWwx`\n\n**IDL Coverage**: Defines instruction discriminators, accounts, and argument schemas for:\n- `create_match` (lines 68+)\n- `cancel_match` (lines 10-66)\n- `join_match`\n- `settle`\n- `request_refund`\n- `timeout_refund`\n- `initialize_config`\n\n**Key Detail**: `create_match` accounts in IDL order:\n1. `creator` (signer, writable, fee payer)\n2. `server` (signer, co-sign authority)\n3. `coinflip_match` (writable, PDA)\n4. `config` (readonly, PDA)\n5. `system_program`\n\n---\n\n### 7. Errors (Coinflip Program)\n\n**Location**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/solana/programs/coinflip/src/error.rs`\n\n**Base Offset**: 6000 (Anchor adds this to all error codes)\n\n| Error Code | Rust Name | Message | Line |\n|------------|-----------|---------|------|\n| 6100 | `InvalidSide` | Invalid side: must be 0 or 1 | 7 |\n| 6101 | `InvalidTier` | Invalid tier index | 11 |\n| 6102 | `InvalidPhase` | Match is not in expected phase | 15 |\n| 6103 | `InsufficientFunds` | Insufficient funds for entry | 19 |\n| 6104 | `CannotJoinOwnMatch` | Creator cannot join their own match | 23 |\n| 6105 | `ServerMismatch` | Server key mismatch | 27 |\n| 6106 | `CommitmentMismatch` | Commitment ≠ SHA256(secret) | 31 |\n| 6107 | `CannotCancel` | Only WAITING phase cancellable | 35 |\n| 6108 | `LockTimeoutNotElapsed` | Timeout not elapsed | 39 |\n| 6109 | `EntropyTooShort` | Entropy < 32 bytes | 43 |\n| 6110 | `DeadlineNotReached` | Resolve deadline not reached | 47 |\n| 6111 | `AccountMismatch` | Account key ≠ expected value | 51 |\n| 6112 | `NotParticipant` | Caller not a participant | 55 |\n| 6113 | `AlreadyVotedRefund` | Caller already voted | 59 |\n\n---\n\n### 8. Backend Service Implementation Status\n\n**Location**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/`\n\n**Status**: COMPLETE (20 iterations + devnet E2E tested)\n\n#### Modules Implemented\n\n| Module | File | Purpose |\n|--------|------|---------|\n| **Config** | `src/config.ts` | Env loader: RPC_URL, DATABASE_URL, SERVER_KEYPAIR, PORT, auth skew, rate limits, worker poll interval |\n| **DB Client** | `src/db.ts` | Postgres wrapper with `rounds` + `operator_events` tables; phase transitions, operator audit trail |\n| **Fairness Utilities** | `src/fairness.ts` | `generateSecret()`, `computeCommitment()`, `deriveMatchPda()` |\n| **TX Builder** | `src/tx-builder.ts` | `buildCreateMatchTx()` — builds + partial-signs create_match with Borsh encoding (no Anchor dep) |\n| **Routes: Create** | `src/routes/create.ts` | `POST /fairness/coinflip/create` — generates secret, builds tx, stores round, returns partial tx + PDA |\n| **Routes: Rounds** | `src/routes/rounds.ts` | `GET /fairness/rounds/:pda` — serves round data, redacts secret for unsettled, includes verification payloads |\n| **Routes: Health** | `src/routes/health.ts` | `GET /health` — status, version, balance, DB connectivity, worker state, unsettled stats |\n| **Auth Middleware** | `src/middleware/auth.ts` | Ed25519 wallet signature verification, timestamp replay protection (60s skew) |\n| **Rate Limit Middleware** | `src/middleware/rate-limit.ts` | Per-wallet (10/min) + global (100/min) sliding-window limits; returns 429 with Retry-After |\n| **Settlement Worker** | `src/worker/settlement.ts` | Polls chain via `getProgramAccounts` (memcmp filters); detects PHASE_LOCKED matches, triggers settle |\n| **Settle TX Builder** | `src/worker/settle-tx.ts` | Builds settle instruction: reads entropy, derives result, calls update_player_profile_cpi, submits tx |\n| **Retry Logic** | `src/worker/retry.ts` | Exponential backoff (2s→4s→8s→16s→30s, 5 max attempts); permanent vs transient error classification |\n| **Logger** | `src/logger.ts` | Structured JSON logging (no secrets ever logged) |\n| **Migrations** | `src/migrate.ts` | Idempotent Postgres migration runner |\n| **Main** | `src/index.ts` | Hono server entry; wires all routes, middleware, worker |\n\n#### Database Schema\n\n**`rounds` table** (23 columns):\n- `pda` (PRIMARY KEY)\n- `game`, `creator`, `server_key`, `tier`, `side`, `nonce`, phase\n- Fairness fields: `secret` (BYTEA), `commitment`, `algorithm_version`\n- Settlement fields: `target_slot`, `settle_tx`, `result_hash`, `result_side`, `winner`\n- Metadata: `settle_attempts`, `created_at`, `updated_at`\n\n**`operator_events` table** (audit trail):\n- `id` (BIGSERIAL PRIMARY KEY)\n- `pda` (nullable)\n- `event_type` (enum: secret_generated, match_detected, settle_submitted, settle_confirmed, settle_failed, timeout_detected, etc.)\n- `payload` (JSONB)\n- `created_at`\n\n**Indexes**: `rounds(phase)`, `rounds(creator)`, `operator_events(pda, created_at)`, `operator_events(event_type, created_at)`\n\n#### Test Coverage\n- **Unit tests** (26 tests): fairness utilities, auth, rate limiting\n- **Integration tests** (4 tests): full create → join → settle lifecycle with mock connection\n- **Endpoint tests** (9 tests): HTTP layer (auth, rate limit, 404, 409, 429 responses)\n- **Total**: 39 tests, all passing\n\n---\n\n## Gap Analysis Summary\n\n### On-Chain Alignment\n- ✓ **Commitment storage**: CoinflipMatch.commitment (32 bytes, set at create_match line 77)\n- ✓ **Algorithm version**: CoinflipMatch.algorithm_ver (set to ALGORITHM_VERSION=1 at line 78)\n- ✓ **Entropy source**: SlotHashes sysvar (ENTROPY_SLOT_OFFSET=12 slots after join, line 60 join_match.rs)\n- ✓ **Target slot**: CoinflipMatch.target_slot (set on join_match line 60)\n- ✓ **Settlement permissionless**: settle instruction has no server signer constraint (anyone can call with secret)\n- ✓ **Result derivation**: derive_result() matches settle's formula (line 92 settle.rs)\n- ✓ **Fairness event**: MatchSettled emitted with all verification data (lines 109-120 settle.rs)\n\n### Backend Implementation Alignment\n- ✓ **Secret generation**: crypto.randomBytes(32) CSPRNG\n- ✓ **Commitment computation**: SHA256(secret) matching packages/fairness\n- ✓ **PDA derivation**: [\"match\", creator, nonce.to_le_bytes()] seeds match on-chain\n- ✓ **Partial signing**: Server co-signs create_match, user is fee payer\n- ✓ **Settlement worker**: Polls getProgramAccounts with phase + server memcmp filters\n- ✓ **Entropy handling**: Reads 32 bytes from SlotHashes sysvar\n- ✓ **Result verification**: Pre-computes result_hash via derive_result before settle\n- ✓ **Retry logic**: Exponential backoff with permanent/transient classification\n- ✓ **Database audit trail**: operator_events logs all state transitions\n- ✓ **Public verification endpoint**: GET /fairness/rounds/:pda serves secrets post-settlement\n\n### Acceptance Criteria Coverage\nAll 7 Functional Requirements (FR-1 through FR-7) marked complete in implementation history:\n1. ✓ FR-1: Secret generation + transaction signing\n2. ✓ FR-2: Settlement worker with retry logic\n3. ✓ FR-3: Round state storage + operator events\n4. ✓ FR-4: Round verification endpoint\n5. ✓ FR-5: Request authentication (wallet signature + timestamp)\n6. ✓ FR-6: Health & observability endpoints\n7. ✓ FR-7: Rate limiting (per-wallet + global)\n\n---\n\n## Files Summary by Type\n\n### On-Chain (Rust)\n- **Instructions**: 7 handlers across 7 files (create_match, join_match, settle, request_refund, timeout_refund, cancel_match, initialize_config)\n- **State**: CoinflipMatch (246 bytes), CoinflipConfig, MatchSettled event\n- **Fairness**: verify_commitment, derive_result, read_mock_entropy (+ error types)\n- **Fees**: calculate_net_payout (3% split: 200 rev / 70 rakeback / 30 chest)\n\n### Off-Chain (TypeScript Backend)\n- **Core**: 14 source files (config, db, fairness, tx-builder, 3 routes, 2 middleware, 3 worker modules, logger, migrate)\n- **Tests**: 4 test files (fairness, auth, rate-limit, integration, endpoints = 39 tests total)\n- **Database**: 2 tables, 4 indexes, migrations versioning\n\n### Frontend/Shared (TypeScript)\n- **Fairness Package**: 2 functions (computeCommitment, verifyCommitment) mirrored on-chain\n- **Anchor Client IDL**: Full instruction definitions for all 7 instructions\n\n---\n\nThis inventory is complete and ready for the gap analysis phase of spec 006-fairness-backend."}],"totalDurationMs":90481,"totalTokens":72436,"totalToolUseCount":30,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":869,"cache_read_input_tokens":66329,"output_tokens":5236,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":869},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
