{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01AjWj6Dy3kJJJmaV1n984WU","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now let me compile a comprehensive inventory report:\n\n## Backend Service Inventory Report\n\n### Directory Structure\n**Path**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/`\n\n### 1. **Package.json & Configuration**\n\n**File**: `services/backend/package.json`\n- **Name**: `@rng-utopia/backend`\n- **Version**: 0.1.0\n- **Type**: ESM (module)\n- **Scripts**:\n  - `dev`: `tsx watch src/index.ts`\n  - `build`: `tsc --noEmit`\n  - `lint`: `eslint .`\n  - `lint:fix`: `eslint . --fix`\n  - `typecheck`: `tsc --noEmit`\n  - `migrate`: `tsx src/migrate.ts`\n  - `migrate:status`: `tsx src/migrate.ts status`\n  - `test`: `vitest --passWithNoTests`\n\n- **Dependencies**:\n  - `@solana/web3.js` (^1.98.0) — Solana blockchain interaction\n  - `bs58` (^6.0.0) — Base58 encoding/decoding\n  - `hono` (^4.6.0) — Web framework\n  - `postgres` (^3.4.0) — PostgreSQL driver\n  - `tweetnacl` (^1.0.3) — Ed25519 cryptography\n\n- **Dev Dependencies**:\n  - `@rng-utopia/config` (workspace:*) — Shared config package\n  - `@types/node` (^22.10.0)\n  - `tsx` (^4.7.0) — TypeScript executor\n  - `typescript` (^5.7.0)\n  - `vitest` (^2.1.0) — Test framework\n\n### 2. **Environment Variables (from config.ts)**\n\n**File**: `services/backend/src/config.ts` — Lines 35-60\n\n**Required Environment Variables**:\n- `DATABASE_URL` — PostgreSQL connection string\n- `RPC_URL` — Solana RPC endpoint\n- `SERVER_KEYPAIR` — JSON array of secret key bytes (from solana-keygen)\n\n**Optional Environment Variables** (with defaults):\n- `PORT` (default: 3100)\n- `AUTH_CLOCK_SKEW_SECONDS` (default: 60) — Clock skew tolerance for request timestamps\n- `RATE_LIMIT_PER_WALLET` (default: 10) — Max POST requests per wallet per minute\n- `RATE_LIMIT_GLOBAL` (default: 100) — Max total POST requests per minute\n- `WORKER_POLL_INTERVAL_MS` (default: 2000) — Settlement worker poll interval\n- `ENTROPY_ACCOUNT` (default: \"SysvarS1otHashes111111111111111111111111111\") — Solana sysvar for entropy\n- `MIN_SOL_BALANCE` (default: 0.1) — Minimum SOL balance threshold for server key\n\n---\n\n### 3. **Core Entry Point**\n\n**File**: `services/backend/src/index.ts` — Lines 1-85\n\n**Exports**: Default Hono app (port, fetch handler)\n\n**Key Functions**:\n- Initializes Hono app\n- Loads config via `loadConfig()`\n- Creates DB pool via `createDb()`\n- Creates Solana `Connection`\n- Registers rate-limit middleware on `/fairness/*` routes\n- Registers auth middleware on `/fairness/*` routes\n- Routes:\n  - `/fairness/coinflip` — Coinflip creation endpoint\n  - `/fairness/rounds` — Round verification/lookup\n  - `/health` — Health check endpoint\n- Starts settlement worker with retry settler\n\n---\n\n### 4. **Database Client**\n\n**File**: `services/backend/src/db.ts` — Lines 1-224\n\n**Types & Exports**:\n\n```typescript\ntype RoundPhase = \"created\" | \"locked\" | \"settling\" | \"settled\" | \"expired\"\n\ntype OperatorEventType =\n  | \"secret_generated\"\n  | \"tx_built\"\n  | \"match_detected\"\n  | \"settle_submitted\"\n  | \"settle_confirmed\"\n  | \"settle_failed\"\n  | \"settle_retried\"\n  | \"timeout_detected\"\n\ninterface Round {\n  pda: string\n  game: string\n  creator: string\n  server_key: string\n  secret: Buffer\n  commitment: Buffer\n  tier: number\n  side: number\n  nonce: string (bigint from DB)\n  phase: RoundPhase\n  target_slot: string | null\n  settle_tx: string | null\n  settle_attempts: number\n  result_hash: Buffer | null\n  result_side: number | null\n  winner: string | null\n  created_at: Date\n  updated_at: Date\n}\n\ninterface OperatorEvent {\n  id: string\n  pda: string | null\n  event_type: OperatorEventType\n  payload: unknown\n  created_at: Date\n}\n```\n\n**Db Interface** (Lines 94-126):\n- `insertRound(params: InsertRoundParams)` → Promise<Round>\n- `updateRoundPhase(pda, newPhase, updates?)` → Promise<Round> (enforces valid transitions)\n- `getRoundByPda(pda)` → Promise<Round | undefined>\n- `getRoundsByPhase(phase)` → Promise<Round[]>\n- `insertOperatorEvent(pda, eventType, payload?)` → Promise<OperatorEvent>\n- `getUnsettledStats()` → Promise<{count, oldestAgeSeconds}>\n- `close()` → Promise<void>\n\n**Valid Phase Transitions** (Lines 73-79):\n- `created` → `locked` or `expired`\n- `locked` → `settling`\n- `settling` → `settled`\n- `settled` (terminal)\n- `expired` (terminal)\n\n**Factory**: `createDb(databaseUrl: string): Db` (Line 128)\n\n---\n\n### 5. **Logger**\n\n**File**: `services/backend/src/logger.ts` — Lines 1-43\n\n**Type**: `LogLevel = \"debug\" | \"info\" | \"warn\" | \"error\"`\n\n**Exports**:\n```typescript\nconst logger = {\n  debug(message, fields?)\n  info(message, fields?)\n  warn(message, fields?)\n  error(message, fields?)\n}\n```\n\n**Behavior**: JSON structured logging to stdout (info/debug/warn) and stderr (error)\n\n---\n\n### 6. **Middleware: Authentication**\n\n**File**: `services/backend/src/middleware/auth.ts` — Lines 1-82\n\n**Export**: `createAuthMiddleware(config: AuthConfig): MiddlewareHandler`\n\n**Function** (Lines 24-82):\n- Skips non-POST requests\n- Expects body: `{wallet, tier, side, nonce, timestamp, signature}`\n- Verifies Ed25519 signature over canonical JSON: `JSON.stringify({wallet, tier, side, nonce, timestamp})`\n- Checks timestamp freshness against `clockSkewSeconds` config\n- Returns 401 on invalid signature/timestamp\n- Returns 400 on missing fields\n- Passes through to next on success\n\n**Signature Encoding**: Base58-encoded 64-byte Ed25519 signature\n\n---\n\n### 7. **Middleware: Rate Limiting**\n\n**File**: `services/backend/src/middleware/rate-limit.ts` — Lines 1-93\n\n**Export**: `createRateLimitMiddleware(config: RateLimitConfig): MiddlewareHandler`\n\n**Function** (Lines 43-93):\n- Applies only to POST requests\n- Per-wallet limiting: keyed by `wallet` field in JSON body\n- Global limiting: all POST requests combined\n- Sliding window implementation (window size configurable)\n- Returns 429 with `Retry-After` header when limits exceeded\n- GET requests bypass rate limiting\n\n**Config Fields**:\n- `perWallet` (default 10) — max POST per wallet per window\n- `global` (default 100) — max total POST per window\n- `windowMs` (default 60_000) — window size in milliseconds\n\n---\n\n### 8. **Transaction Builder**\n\n**File**: `services/backend/src/tx-builder.ts` — Lines 1-127\n\n**Exports**:\n\n```typescript\ninterface BuildCreateMatchTxParams {\n  connection: Connection\n  creator: PublicKey\n  serverKeypair: Keypair\n  commitment: Buffer\n  tier: number\n  side: number\n  nonce: bigint\n}\n\ninterface BuildCreateMatchTxResult {\n  transaction: string (base64)\n  matchPda: PublicKey\n}\n```\n\n**Key Functions**:\n\n- `encodeCreateMatchData(commitment, tier, side, nonce): Buffer` (Lines 31-55) — Borsh encodes 50-byte instruction data with discriminator + commitment + tier + side + nonce\n- `deriveConfigPda(): [PublicKey, number]` (Lines 20-25) — Derives `[\"coinflip_config\"]` PDA under COINFLIP_PROGRAM_ID\n- `buildCreateMatchTx(params): Promise<BuildCreateMatchTxResult>` (Lines 82-127) — Builds, partially signs with server key, returns base64-serialized tx\n\n**Constants**:\n- `CREATE_MATCH_DISCRIMINATOR` (Lines 15-17) — `[107, 2, 184, 145, 70, 142, 17, 165]`\n\n---\n\n### 9. **Fairness Utilities**\n\n**File**: `services/backend/src/fairness.ts` — Lines 1-35\n\n**Exports**:\n\n- `COINFLIP_PROGRAM_ID` = `new PublicKey(\"BdHFeqmkYe7znXV1Avk3zz496Pjo8QhEDN4MKPUTAWwx\")`\n- `generateSecret(): Buffer` — 32-byte cryptographically secure random\n- `computeCommitment(secret: Buffer): Buffer` — SHA256(secret)\n- `deriveMatchPda(creator: PublicKey, nonce: number | bigint): [PublicKey, number]` — Seeds: `[\"match\", creator, nonce_le_bytes]`\n\n---\n\n### 10. **Routes: Coinflip Creation**\n\n**File**: `services/backend/src/routes/create.ts` — Lines 1-180\n\n**Export**: `createCoinflipRoutes(deps: CreateRoutesDeps): Hono`\n\n**POST /fairness/coinflip/create** (Lines 80-177):\n\n1. Parse & validate request body (Lines 82-91)\n   - `wallet`: base58 public key\n   - `tier`: 0-255 integer\n   - `side`: 0 or 1\n   - `nonce`: non-negative integer\n   - `timestamp`: unix seconds integer\n   - `signature`: non-empty string\n\n2. Validate wallet is PublicKey (Lines 93-99)\n\n3. Generate secret & commitment (Lines 101-103)\n\n4. Derive match PDA (Line 106)\n\n5. Check for duplicate PDA in DB (Lines 109-116) → return 409 if exists\n\n6. Build & partially-sign tx (Lines 118-136)\n\n7. Insert round to DB with phase \"created\" (Lines 138-161)\n\n8. Log operator event \"secret_generated\" (Lines 163-169)\n\n9. Return `{transaction, matchPda, commitment}` (Lines 171-176)\n\n**Status Codes**:\n- 200: Success\n- 400: Invalid request body\n- 409: Duplicate nonce\n- 500: TX build failure\n\n---\n\n### 11. **Routes: Round Verification**\n\n**File**: `services/backend/src/routes/rounds.ts` — Lines 1-69\n\n**Export**: `createRoundsRoutes(deps: RoundsRoutesDeps): Hono`\n\n**GET /fairness/rounds/:pda** (Lines 57-66):\n\n- Queries DB for round by PDA\n- Returns 404 if not found\n- Formats response (Lines 16-50):\n  - Converts snake_case to camelCase\n  - Redacts `secret` if phase != \"settled\"\n  - Includes verification payload for settled rounds only:\n    ```json\n    {\n      \"commitmentCheck\": \"sha256(secret) == commitment\",\n      \"resultFormula\": \"sha256(secret || entropy || pda || algorithmVersion)\",\n      \"entropySource\": \"SlotHashes sysvar at target_slot\"\n    }\n    ```\n\n---\n\n### 12. **Routes: Health Check**\n\n**File**: `services/backend/src/routes/health.ts` — Lines 1-72\n\n**Export**: `createHealthRoutes(deps: HealthDeps): Hono`\n\n**GET /health** (Lines 25-68):\n\nReturns:\n```json\n{\n  \"status\": \"ok\",\n  \"version\": \"0.1.0\",\n  \"serverKey\": \"<base58 pubkey>\",\n  \"solBalance\": <number (SOL)>,\n  \"dbConnected\": <bool>,\n  \"workerRunning\": <bool>,\n  \"unsettledCount\": <number>,\n  \"oldestUnsettledAge\": <number (seconds)>\n}\n```\n\n- Queries `db.getUnsettledStats()` for count & age (Lines 31-38)\n- Fetches server key balance from RPC (Lines 40-47)\n- Warns if balance < `minSolBalance` (Lines 49-56)\n\n---\n\n### 13. **Settlement Worker**\n\n**File**: `services/backend/src/worker/settlement.ts` — Lines 1-134\n\n**Export**: `createSettlementWorker(deps: SettlementWorkerDeps): SettlementWorker`\n\n**SettlementWorker Interface** (Lines 29-34):\n- `start(): void` — Start polling\n- `stop(): void` — Stop polling\n- `isRunning: boolean` (getter)\n- `poll(): Promise<void>` — Run single poll cycle (exposed for testing)\n\n**Poll Logic** (Lines 45-99):\n\n1. Get current slot from RPC\n2. Query chain for PHASE_LOCKED (`1`) CoinflipMatch accounts:\n   - Filter by account size 246 bytes\n   - Filter by phase == LOCKED at offset 114\n   - Filter by server key at offset 72\n3. For each discovered match:\n   - Read target_slot (u64 LE at offset 148)\n   - Transition DB round from \"created\" → \"locked\" (if first discovery)\n   - Log \"match_detected\" event\n4. If current_slot >= target_slot:\n   - Call `onSettleReady(pda)` callback\n\n**Account Layout Offsets**:\n- Discriminator: 0-8\n- Server key: 72-104 (32 bytes)\n- Phase: 114 (1 byte)\n- Target slot: 148-156 (u64 LE)\n\n---\n\n### 14. **Settlement Transaction Builder & Submission**\n\n**File**: `services/backend/src/worker/settle-tx.ts` — Lines 1-302\n\n**Exports**:\n\n```typescript\ninterface SettleTxDeps {\n  db: Db\n  connection: Connection\n  serverKeypair: Keypair\n  entropyAccount: PublicKey\n}\n\ninterface SettleResult {\n  txSignature: string\n  resultHash: Buffer\n  resultSide: number\n  winner: string\n}\n\nclass PermanentSettleError extends Error\nclass TransientSettleError extends Error\n```\n\n**Export Function**: `settleMatch(deps: SettleTxDeps, pda: string): Promise<SettleResult>` (Lines 129-279)\n\n**Steps**:\n\n1. Retrieve secret from DB (Lines 136-152)\n   - Throw `PermanentSettleError` if not found\n   - Transition \"locked\" → \"settling\" if needed\n   - Log \"settle_submitted\" event\n\n2. Fetch match account from chain (Lines 159-173)\n   - Parse creator (offset 8, 32 bytes)\n   - Parse opponent (offset 40, 32 bytes)\n   - Parse creatorSide (offset 113, 1 byte)\n   - Parse algoVer (offset 147, 1 byte)\n\n3. Fetch config account (Lines 175-187)\n   - Parse treasury (offset 40, 32 bytes)\n\n4. Read entropy from entropy account (Lines 189-194)\n   - First 32 bytes of account data\n\n5. Pre-compute result (Lines 196-200)\n   - `resultHash = SHA256(secret || entropy || matchPda || algoVer)`\n   - `resultSide = resultHash[0] % 2`\n   - `winner = resultSide == creatorSide ? creator : opponent`\n\n6. Derive player profile PDAs (Lines 202-204)\n\n7. Build settle instruction (Lines 206-233)\n   - Discriminator: `[175, 42, 185, 87, 144, 131, 102, 212]`\n   - 40-byte data: discriminator(8) + secret(32)\n   - Accounts: server, match, config, entropy, treasury, creator, opponent, creator_profile, opponent_profile, platform_program, system_program\n\n8. Fetch latest blockhash, build tx, sign with server key (Lines 235-244)\n\n9. Submit & confirm (Lines 246-255)\n\n10. Update DB phase \"settling\" → \"settled\" (Lines 257-264)\n    - Store: settle_tx, result_hash, result_side, winner, settle_attempts\n    - Log \"settle_confirmed\" event\n\n**Constants**:\n- `PLATFORM_PROGRAM_ID` = `\"85qwC1cDpSYkBBHUcN4nuZ119hCx4N94X38GjAHxnWjA\"`\n- `SETTLE_DISCRIMINATOR` = `[175, 42, 185, 87, 144, 131, 102, 212]`\n\n**Account Offsets**:\n- Creator: 8\n- Opponent: 40\n- Creator side: 113\n- Algo version: 147\n\n---\n\n### 15. **Retry Settlement Logic**\n\n**File**: `services/backend/src/worker/retry.ts` — Lines 1-182\n\n**Export**: `createRetrySettler(deps: RetrySettlerDeps): RetrySettler`\n\n**RetrySettler Interface** (Lines 42-50):\n- `attemptSettle(pda: string): Promise<void>` — Attempt settlement with retry logic\n\n**Retry Logic** (Lines 93-178):\n\n1. Skip if PDA already marked as permanently failed or timed out\n2. Check if retry is scheduled but not yet due — skip if so\n3. If max retries (5) exceeded:\n   - Mark as failed\n   - Log \"settle_failed\" event\n   - Return\n4. Check if resolve_deadline (on-chain, offset 156) has passed:\n   - Mark as timeout\n   - Log \"timeout_detected\" event\n   - Return\n5. Attempt `settleMatch(pda)`:\n   - On success: clear retry state, log \"match settled\"\n   - On `PermanentSettleError`: mark failed, log error\n   - On transient error: schedule retry with exponential backoff (base 2s, max 30s)\n\n**Constants**:\n- `MAX_RETRIES` = 5\n- `BASE_DELAY_MS` = 2000\n- `MAX_DELAY_MS` = 30000\n- `RESOLVE_DEADLINE_OFFSET` = 156 (i64 LE in match account)\n\n---\n\n### 16. **Migration Runner**\n\n**File**: `services/backend/src/migrate.ts` — Lines 1-137\n\n**Exports**:\n- `runMigrations(databaseUrl: string): Promise<void>` (Lines 77-102)\n- `showStatus(databaseUrl: string): Promise<void>` (Lines 104-121)\n\n**CLI Usage**:\n- `tsx src/migrate.ts` — Run pending migrations\n- `tsx src/migrate.ts status` — Show migration status\n\n**Behavior** (Lines 60-75):\n1. Ensures `_migrations` tracking table exists\n2. Loads `.sql` files from `../migrations/` directory (sorted by version)\n3. For each pending migration:\n   - Runs SQL in a transaction with `sql.unsafe(content)`\n   - Records version in `_migrations` table\n4. Idempotent: skips already-applied migrations\n\n**Tracking Table**:\n```sql\nCREATE TABLE _migrations (\n  version INT PRIMARY KEY,\n  name TEXT NOT NULL,\n  applied_at TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT now()\n)\n```\n\n---\n\n### 17. **Database Migration**\n\n**File**: `services/backend/migrations/001_init.sql` — Lines 1-36\n\n**Schema**:\n\n**rounds table**:\n```sql\nCREATE TABLE rounds (\n  pda TEXT PRIMARY KEY,\n  game TEXT NOT NULL,\n  creator TEXT NOT NULL,\n  server_key TEXT NOT NULL,\n  secret BYTEA NOT NULL,\n  commitment BYTEA NOT NULL,\n  tier SMALLINT NOT NULL,\n  side SMALLINT NOT NULL,\n  nonce BIGINT NOT NULL,\n  phase TEXT NOT NULL,\n  target_slot BIGINT,\n  settle_tx TEXT,\n  settle_attempts INT DEFAULT 0,\n  result_hash BYTEA,\n  result_side SMALLINT,\n  winner TEXT,\n  created_at TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT now(),\n  updated_at TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT now()\n)\n```\n\n**operator_events table**:\n```sql\nCREATE TABLE operator_events (\n  id BIGSERIAL PRIMARY KEY,\n  pda TEXT,\n  event_type TEXT NOT NULL,\n  payload JSONB,\n  created_at TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT now()\n)\n```\n\n**Indexes**:\n- `idx_rounds_phase` on `rounds(phase)`\n- `idx_rounds_creator` on `rounds(creator)`\n- `idx_operator_events_pda_created` on `operator_events(pda, created_at)`\n- `idx_operator_events_type_created` on `operator_events(event_type, created_at)`\n\n---\n\n## 18. **Test Files**\n\n### 18a. **Auth Middleware Tests**\n\n**File**: `services/backend/src/__tests__/auth.test.ts` — Lines 1-137\n\n**Test Suite**: \"auth middleware\"\n\n**Tests** (total 8):\n1. `accepts a valid signature` (L58-63) — 200 response\n2. `rejects an invalid (zeroed) signature` (L65-71) — 401 response\n3. `rejects a signature from the wrong keypair` (L73-95) — 401 response\n4. `rejects an expired timestamp` (L97-104) — 401 when > 60s old\n5. `accepts a timestamp within clock skew` (L106-113) — 200 when within 60s\n6. `rejects a missing signature field` (L115-121) — 401 response\n7. `rejects a missing timestamp field` (L123-130) — 401 response\n8. `passes GET requests without authentication` (L132-136) — 200 (bypassed auth)\n\n**Helper**: `makeSignedRequest()` constructs canonical payload and signs with tweetnacl\n\n---\n\n### 18b. **Rate Limit Middleware Tests**\n\n**File**: `services/backend/src/__tests__/rate-limit.test.ts` — Lines 1-88\n\n**Test Suite**: \"rate-limit middleware\"\n\n**Tests** (total 7):\n1. `allows requests within per-wallet limit` (L24-30) — 3 requests, all 200\n2. `blocks requests exceeding per-wallet limit` (L32-38) — 2 allowed, 3rd is 429\n3. `returns Retry-After header on per-wallet 429` (L40-46) — Header value = \"60\"\n4. `tracks wallets independently` (L48-60) — Different wallets have separate limits\n5. `enforces global limit across all wallets` (L62-69) — Global limit applies across wallets\n6. `returns correct Retry-After seconds based on window` (L71-77) — 30s window → \"30\" header\n7. `does not rate-limit GET requests` (L79-86) — GET bypasses limiting\n\n---\n\n### 18c. **Fairness Utilities Tests**\n\n**File**: `services/backend/src/__tests__/fairness.test.ts` — Lines 1-105\n\n**Test Suites**: 3 functions tested\n\n**generateSecret tests** (3):\n1. `returns a 32-byte buffer` (L7-11) — Verify length & type\n2. `produces unique secrets on successive calls` (L13-18) — Randomness check\n\n**computeCommitment tests** (5):\n1. `returns sha256 of the secret bytes` (L20-27) — Known SHA256 constant\n2. `matches the packages/fairness commitment algorithm` (L29-43) — Cross-check with Node crypto\n3. `is deterministic` (L45-50) — Same secret → same commitment\n4. `produces different commitments for different secrets` (L52-56) — Different secrets → different commitments\n\n**deriveMatchPda tests** (6):\n1. `returns a PublicKey and bump seed` (L65-71) — Type & range check\n2. `matches manual PDA derivation with seeds [match, creator, nonce_le]` (L73-85) — Cross-check with manual derivation\n3. `accepts bigint nonce` (L87-91) — Both number & bigint accepted\n4. `produces different PDAs for different nonces` (L93-97) — Different nonce → different PDA\n5. `produces different PDAs for different creators` (L99-104) — Different creator → different PDA\n\n---\n\n### 18d. **HTTP Endpoint Tests**\n\n**File**: `services/backend/src/__tests__/endpoints.test.ts` — Lines 1-379\n\n**Fixtures**:\n- Mock Connection class (Lines 46-57)\n- Test constants: `DATABASE_URL`, `TIER_IRON`, `SIDE_HEADS`\n- Auth helper: `signCreateRequest()` (Lines 63-77)\n\n**Test Suite**: \"HTTP endpoint tests\" (3 nested suites)\n\n**POST /fairness/coinflip/create tests** (5):\n1. `returns 200 with valid auth` (L167-189) — Verify response shape\n2. `returns 401 with invalid signature` (L191-208) — Wrong keypair signature\n3. `returns 401 with expired timestamp` (L210-226) — 120s in past\n4. `returns 409 with duplicate nonce` (L228-254) — Same nonce twice\n5. `returns 429 when rate limit exceeded` (L256-285) — Limit 2 per wallet, 3rd blocked\n\n**GET /fairness/rounds/:pda tests** (2):\n1. `returns 200 for known PDA` (L293-325) — Full response shape check, secret redacted for unsettled\n2. `returns 404 for unknown PDA` (L327-334) — Error response\n\n**GET /health tests** (2):\n1. `returns 200 with expected fields` (L342-357) — All response fields present & types correct\n2. `reflects unsettled round count` (L359-377) — Count increments after creating round\n\n---\n\n### 18e. **Integration Test**\n\n**File**: `services/backend/src/__tests__/integration.test.ts` — Lines 1-562\n\n**Test Suite**: \"Integration: create → join → settle lifecycle\"\n\n**Mock Connection Class** (Lines 49-172):\n- Simulates on-chain state in-memory\n- Methods: `setAccount()`, `removeAccount()`, `getLatestBlockhash()`, `getSlot()`, `getAccountInfo()`, `getProgramAccounts()`, `sendRawTransaction()`, `confirmTransaction()`, `getBalance()`\n- Supports memcmp filters for querying accounts by field values\n\n**Account Data Builders** (Lines 177-227):\n- `buildMatchAccountData()` — 246-byte CoinflipMatch account with all fields\n- `buildConfigAccountData()` — 74-byte CoinflipConfig with treasury address\n\n**Tests** (4):\n1. `full lifecycle: create → join (mock) → settle → verify` (L327-500)\n   - Create round via POST /fairness/coinflip/create\n   - Verify DB state in \"created\" phase\n   - Simulate on-chain join by adding PHASE_LOCKED match to mock\n   - Trigger settlement worker poll\n   - Verify DB transitioned to \"settled\" with result data\n   - Verify operator event trail includes all events\n   - Verify GET /fairness/rounds/:pda now includes secret & verification\n\n2. `GET /rounds/:pda returns 404 for unknown PDA` (L502-506) — 404 response\n\n3. `unsettled round does not expose secret` (L508-532) — Secret & verification redacted for \"created\" phase\n\n4. `duplicate nonce returns 409` (L534-561) — Second request with same nonce → 409\n\n---\n\n## Summary Table\n\n| Component | File | Key Exports | Lines |\n|-----------|------|-------------|-------|\n| **Config** | `config.ts` | `Config`, `loadConfig()` | 1-60 |\n| **DB Client** | `db.ts` | `Db`, `Round`, `OperatorEvent`, `RoundPhase`, `createDb()` | 1-224 |\n| **Logger** | `logger.ts` | `logger`, `LogLevel` | 1-43 |\n| **Auth Middleware** | `middleware/auth.ts` | `createAuthMiddleware()` | 1-82 |\n| **Rate Limit Middleware** | `middleware/rate-limit.ts` | `createRateLimitMiddleware()` | 1-93 |\n| **TX Builder** | `tx-builder.ts` | `buildCreateMatchTx()`, `BuildCreateMatchTxResult` | 1-127 |\n| **Fairness Utils** | `fairness.ts` | `generateSecret()`, `computeCommitment()`, `deriveMatchPda()`, `COINFLIP_PROGRAM_ID` | 1-35 |\n| **Coinflip Routes** | `routes/create.ts` | `createCoinflipRoutes()` | 1-180 |\n| **Rounds Routes** | `routes/rounds.ts` | `createRoundsRoutes()` | 1-69 |\n| **Health Routes** | `routes/health.ts` | `createHealthRoutes()` | 1-72 |\n| **Settlement Worker** | `worker/settlement.ts` | `createSettlementWorker()`, `SettlementWorker` | 1-134 |\n| **Settle TX** | `worker/settle-tx.ts` | `settleMatch()`, `SettleResult`, `PermanentSettleError`, `TransientSettleError` | 1-302 |\n| **Retry Settler** | `worker/retry.ts` | `createRetrySettler()`, `RetrySettler` | 1-182 |\n| **Migrations** | `migrate.ts` | `runMigrations()`, `showStatus()` | 1-137 |\n| **SQL Migration** | `migrations/001_init.sql` | `rounds`, `operator_events` tables | 1-36 |\n\n---\n\n## Key Architectural Insights\n\n1. **3-Layer Request Flow**:\n   - Rate limit → Auth signature verification → Route handler\n\n2. **Database-Centric Settlement**:\n   - DB stores secrets (created phase)\n   - Worker detects locked matches on-chain\n   - Settler reads secret from DB, computes result, submits settlement tx\n   - Retry logic with exponential backoff (2s-30s, max 5 attempts)\n\n3. **Phase Machine** (4 states):\n   - `created` → `locked` (detected on-chain)\n   - `locked` → `settling` (settlement starting)\n   - `settling` → `settled` (confirmation received)\n   - `created` → `expired` (timeout fallback)\n\n4. **Audit Trail**:\n   - All state changes logged to `operator_events` table with timestamps & payloads\n   - Enables debugging & fairness verification\n\n5. **Cryptographic Primitives**:\n   - Secret: 32-byte random (generated server-side)\n   - Commitment: SHA256(secret) (shared with client)\n   - Result: SHA256(secret || entropy || pda || algoVer) (derived during settlement)\n\n6. **On-Chain Program IDs**:\n   - Coinflip: `BdHFeqmkYe7znXV1Avk3zz496Pjo8QhEDN4MKPUTAWwx`\n   - Platform: `85qwC1cDpSYkBBHUcN4nuZ119hCx4N94X38GjAHxnWjA`\n   - Entropy: SysvarS1otHashes or custom account\n\nThis backend is a fairness-as-a-service system managing the server's role in commit-reveal coinflip games with off-chain secret storage and on-chain settlement."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a99eb2417baa32638 (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 86356\ntool_uses: 37\nduration_ms: 177283</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c9591fb4-7b0c-48b9-bca6-a93e05209d51","uuid":"147b9463-e6b6-47fc-a2e8-b20bb813c3ee","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Thoroughly inventory the `services/backend/` directory in the codebase at `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/`. I need:\n\n1. **All source files** with their exports/functions — read each `.ts` file in `src/` and subdirectories\n2. **All test files** — read each test file, list test names and what they test\n3. **Migration files** — list SQL files and their contents\n4. **Package.json** — dependencies and scripts\n5. **Config** — what env vars are read\n\nFor each source file, I need:\n- File path (relative to monorepo root)\n- Key exports (function names, classes, types)\n- Line numbers for important function definitions\n\nBe thorough — read every file. This is for a gap analysis audit.","agentId":"a99eb2417baa32638","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now let me compile a comprehensive inventory report:\n\n## Backend Service Inventory Report\n\n### Directory Structure\n**Path**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/`\n\n### 1. **Package.json & Configuration**\n\n**File**: `services/backend/package.json`\n- **Name**: `@rng-utopia/backend`\n- **Version**: 0.1.0\n- **Type**: ESM (module)\n- **Scripts**:\n  - `dev`: `tsx watch src/index.ts`\n  - `build`: `tsc --noEmit`\n  - `lint`: `eslint .`\n  - `lint:fix`: `eslint . --fix`\n  - `typecheck`: `tsc --noEmit`\n  - `migrate`: `tsx src/migrate.ts`\n  - `migrate:status`: `tsx src/migrate.ts status`\n  - `test`: `vitest --passWithNoTests`\n\n- **Dependencies**:\n  - `@solana/web3.js` (^1.98.0) — Solana blockchain interaction\n  - `bs58` (^6.0.0) — Base58 encoding/decoding\n  - `hono` (^4.6.0) — Web framework\n  - `postgres` (^3.4.0) — PostgreSQL driver\n  - `tweetnacl` (^1.0.3) — Ed25519 cryptography\n\n- **Dev Dependencies**:\n  - `@rng-utopia/config` (workspace:*) — Shared config package\n  - `@types/node` (^22.10.0)\n  - `tsx` (^4.7.0) — TypeScript executor\n  - `typescript` (^5.7.0)\n  - `vitest` (^2.1.0) — Test framework\n\n### 2. **Environment Variables (from config.ts)**\n\n**File**: `services/backend/src/config.ts` — Lines 35-60\n\n**Required Environment Variables**:\n- `DATABASE_URL` — PostgreSQL connection string\n- `RPC_URL` — Solana RPC endpoint\n- `SERVER_KEYPAIR` — JSON array of secret key bytes (from solana-keygen)\n\n**Optional Environment Variables** (with defaults):\n- `PORT` (default: 3100)\n- `AUTH_CLOCK_SKEW_SECONDS` (default: 60) — Clock skew tolerance for request timestamps\n- `RATE_LIMIT_PER_WALLET` (default: 10) — Max POST requests per wallet per minute\n- `RATE_LIMIT_GLOBAL` (default: 100) — Max total POST requests per minute\n- `WORKER_POLL_INTERVAL_MS` (default: 2000) — Settlement worker poll interval\n- `ENTROPY_ACCOUNT` (default: \"SysvarS1otHashes111111111111111111111111111\") — Solana sysvar for entropy\n- `MIN_SOL_BALANCE` (default: 0.1) — Minimum SOL balance threshold for server key\n\n---\n\n### 3. **Core Entry Point**\n\n**File**: `services/backend/src/index.ts` — Lines 1-85\n\n**Exports**: Default Hono app (port, fetch handler)\n\n**Key Functions**:\n- Initializes Hono app\n- Loads config via `loadConfig()`\n- Creates DB pool via `createDb()`\n- Creates Solana `Connection`\n- Registers rate-limit middleware on `/fairness/*` routes\n- Registers auth middleware on `/fairness/*` routes\n- Routes:\n  - `/fairness/coinflip` — Coinflip creation endpoint\n  - `/fairness/rounds` — Round verification/lookup\n  - `/health` — Health check endpoint\n- Starts settlement worker with retry settler\n\n---\n\n### 4. **Database Client**\n\n**File**: `services/backend/src/db.ts` — Lines 1-224\n\n**Types & Exports**:\n\n```typescript\ntype RoundPhase = \"created\" | \"locked\" | \"settling\" | \"settled\" | \"expired\"\n\ntype OperatorEventType =\n  | \"secret_generated\"\n  | \"tx_built\"\n  | \"match_detected\"\n  | \"settle_submitted\"\n  | \"settle_confirmed\"\n  | \"settle_failed\"\n  | \"settle_retried\"\n  | \"timeout_detected\"\n\ninterface Round {\n  pda: string\n  game: string\n  creator: string\n  server_key: string\n  secret: Buffer\n  commitment: Buffer\n  tier: number\n  side: number\n  nonce: string (bigint from DB)\n  phase: RoundPhase\n  target_slot: string | null\n  settle_tx: string | null\n  settle_attempts: number\n  result_hash: Buffer | null\n  result_side: number | null\n  winner: string | null\n  created_at: Date\n  updated_at: Date\n}\n\ninterface OperatorEvent {\n  id: string\n  pda: string | null\n  event_type: OperatorEventType\n  payload: unknown\n  created_at: Date\n}\n```\n\n**Db Interface** (Lines 94-126):\n- `insertRound(params: InsertRoundParams)` → Promise<Round>\n- `updateRoundPhase(pda, newPhase, updates?)` → Promise<Round> (enforces valid transitions)\n- `getRoundByPda(pda)` → Promise<Round | undefined>\n- `getRoundsByPhase(phase)` → Promise<Round[]>\n- `insertOperatorEvent(pda, eventType, payload?)` → Promise<OperatorEvent>\n- `getUnsettledStats()` → Promise<{count, oldestAgeSeconds}>\n- `close()` → Promise<void>\n\n**Valid Phase Transitions** (Lines 73-79):\n- `created` → `locked` or `expired`\n- `locked` → `settling`\n- `settling` → `settled`\n- `settled` (terminal)\n- `expired` (terminal)\n\n**Factory**: `createDb(databaseUrl: string): Db` (Line 128)\n\n---\n\n### 5. **Logger**\n\n**File**: `services/backend/src/logger.ts` — Lines 1-43\n\n**Type**: `LogLevel = \"debug\" | \"info\" | \"warn\" | \"error\"`\n\n**Exports**:\n```typescript\nconst logger = {\n  debug(message, fields?)\n  info(message, fields?)\n  warn(message, fields?)\n  error(message, fields?)\n}\n```\n\n**Behavior**: JSON structured logging to stdout (info/debug/warn) and stderr (error)\n\n---\n\n### 6. **Middleware: Authentication**\n\n**File**: `services/backend/src/middleware/auth.ts` — Lines 1-82\n\n**Export**: `createAuthMiddleware(config: AuthConfig): MiddlewareHandler`\n\n**Function** (Lines 24-82):\n- Skips non-POST requests\n- Expects body: `{wallet, tier, side, nonce, timestamp, signature}`\n- Verifies Ed25519 signature over canonical JSON: `JSON.stringify({wallet, tier, side, nonce, timestamp})`\n- Checks timestamp freshness against `clockSkewSeconds` config\n- Returns 401 on invalid signature/timestamp\n- Returns 400 on missing fields\n- Passes through to next on success\n\n**Signature Encoding**: Base58-encoded 64-byte Ed25519 signature\n\n---\n\n### 7. **Middleware: Rate Limiting**\n\n**File**: `services/backend/src/middleware/rate-limit.ts` — Lines 1-93\n\n**Export**: `createRateLimitMiddleware(config: RateLimitConfig): MiddlewareHandler`\n\n**Function** (Lines 43-93):\n- Applies only to POST requests\n- Per-wallet limiting: keyed by `wallet` field in JSON body\n- Global limiting: all POST requests combined\n- Sliding window implementation (window size configurable)\n- Returns 429 with `Retry-After` header when limits exceeded\n- GET requests bypass rate limiting\n\n**Config Fields**:\n- `perWallet` (default 10) — max POST per wallet per window\n- `global` (default 100) — max total POST per window\n- `windowMs` (default 60_000) — window size in milliseconds\n\n---\n\n### 8. **Transaction Builder**\n\n**File**: `services/backend/src/tx-builder.ts` — Lines 1-127\n\n**Exports**:\n\n```typescript\ninterface BuildCreateMatchTxParams {\n  connection: Connection\n  creator: PublicKey\n  serverKeypair: Keypair\n  commitment: Buffer\n  tier: number\n  side: number\n  nonce: bigint\n}\n\ninterface BuildCreateMatchTxResult {\n  transaction: string (base64)\n  matchPda: PublicKey\n}\n```\n\n**Key Functions**:\n\n- `encodeCreateMatchData(commitment, tier, side, nonce): Buffer` (Lines 31-55) — Borsh encodes 50-byte instruction data with discriminator + commitment + tier + side + nonce\n- `deriveConfigPda(): [PublicKey, number]` (Lines 20-25) — Derives `[\"coinflip_config\"]` PDA under COINFLIP_PROGRAM_ID\n- `buildCreateMatchTx(params): Promise<BuildCreateMatchTxResult>` (Lines 82-127) — Builds, partially signs with server key, returns base64-serialized tx\n\n**Constants**:\n- `CREATE_MATCH_DISCRIMINATOR` (Lines 15-17) — `[107, 2, 184, 145, 70, 142, 17, 165]`\n\n---\n\n### 9. **Fairness Utilities**\n\n**File**: `services/backend/src/fairness.ts` — Lines 1-35\n\n**Exports**:\n\n- `COINFLIP_PROGRAM_ID` = `new PublicKey(\"BdHFeqmkYe7znXV1Avk3zz496Pjo8QhEDN4MKPUTAWwx\")`\n- `generateSecret(): Buffer` — 32-byte cryptographically secure random\n- `computeCommitment(secret: Buffer): Buffer` — SHA256(secret)\n- `deriveMatchPda(creator: PublicKey, nonce: number | bigint): [PublicKey, number]` — Seeds: `[\"match\", creator, nonce_le_bytes]`\n\n---\n\n### 10. **Routes: Coinflip Creation**\n\n**File**: `services/backend/src/routes/create.ts` — Lines 1-180\n\n**Export**: `createCoinflipRoutes(deps: CreateRoutesDeps): Hono`\n\n**POST /fairness/coinflip/create** (Lines 80-177):\n\n1. Parse & validate request body (Lines 82-91)\n   - `wallet`: base58 public key\n   - `tier`: 0-255 integer\n   - `side`: 0 or 1\n   - `nonce`: non-negative integer\n   - `timestamp`: unix seconds integer\n   - `signature`: non-empty string\n\n2. Validate wallet is PublicKey (Lines 93-99)\n\n3. Generate secret & commitment (Lines 101-103)\n\n4. Derive match PDA (Line 106)\n\n5. Check for duplicate PDA in DB (Lines 109-116) → return 409 if exists\n\n6. Build & partially-sign tx (Lines 118-136)\n\n7. Insert round to DB with phase \"created\" (Lines 138-161)\n\n8. Log operator event \"secret_generated\" (Lines 163-169)\n\n9. Return `{transaction, matchPda, commitment}` (Lines 171-176)\n\n**Status Codes**:\n- 200: Success\n- 400: Invalid request body\n- 409: Duplicate nonce\n- 500: TX build failure\n\n---\n\n### 11. **Routes: Round Verification**\n\n**File**: `services/backend/src/routes/rounds.ts` — Lines 1-69\n\n**Export**: `createRoundsRoutes(deps: RoundsRoutesDeps): Hono`\n\n**GET /fairness/rounds/:pda** (Lines 57-66):\n\n- Queries DB for round by PDA\n- Returns 404 if not found\n- Formats response (Lines 16-50):\n  - Converts snake_case to camelCase\n  - Redacts `secret` if phase != \"settled\"\n  - Includes verification payload for settled rounds only:\n    ```json\n    {\n      \"commitmentCheck\": \"sha256(secret) == commitment\",\n      \"resultFormula\": \"sha256(secret || entropy || pda || algorithmVersion)\",\n      \"entropySource\": \"SlotHashes sysvar at target_slot\"\n    }\n    ```\n\n---\n\n### 12. **Routes: Health Check**\n\n**File**: `services/backend/src/routes/health.ts` — Lines 1-72\n\n**Export**: `createHealthRoutes(deps: HealthDeps): Hono`\n\n**GET /health** (Lines 25-68):\n\nReturns:\n```json\n{\n  \"status\": \"ok\",\n  \"version\": \"0.1.0\",\n  \"serverKey\": \"<base58 pubkey>\",\n  \"solBalance\": <number (SOL)>,\n  \"dbConnected\": <bool>,\n  \"workerRunning\": <bool>,\n  \"unsettledCount\": <number>,\n  \"oldestUnsettledAge\": <number (seconds)>\n}\n```\n\n- Queries `db.getUnsettledStats()` for count & age (Lines 31-38)\n- Fetches server key balance from RPC (Lines 40-47)\n- Warns if balance < `minSolBalance` (Lines 49-56)\n\n---\n\n### 13. **Settlement Worker**\n\n**File**: `services/backend/src/worker/settlement.ts` — Lines 1-134\n\n**Export**: `createSettlementWorker(deps: SettlementWorkerDeps): SettlementWorker`\n\n**SettlementWorker Interface** (Lines 29-34):\n- `start(): void` — Start polling\n- `stop(): void` — Stop polling\n- `isRunning: boolean` (getter)\n- `poll(): Promise<void>` — Run single poll cycle (exposed for testing)\n\n**Poll Logic** (Lines 45-99):\n\n1. Get current slot from RPC\n2. Query chain for PHASE_LOCKED (`1`) CoinflipMatch accounts:\n   - Filter by account size 246 bytes\n   - Filter by phase == LOCKED at offset 114\n   - Filter by server key at offset 72\n3. For each discovered match:\n   - Read target_slot (u64 LE at offset 148)\n   - Transition DB round from \"created\" → \"locked\" (if first discovery)\n   - Log \"match_detected\" event\n4. If current_slot >= target_slot:\n   - Call `onSettleReady(pda)` callback\n\n**Account Layout Offsets**:\n- Discriminator: 0-8\n- Server key: 72-104 (32 bytes)\n- Phase: 114 (1 byte)\n- Target slot: 148-156 (u64 LE)\n\n---\n\n### 14. **Settlement Transaction Builder & Submission**\n\n**File**: `services/backend/src/worker/settle-tx.ts` — Lines 1-302\n\n**Exports**:\n\n```typescript\ninterface SettleTxDeps {\n  db: Db\n  connection: Connection\n  serverKeypair: Keypair\n  entropyAccount: PublicKey\n}\n\ninterface SettleResult {\n  txSignature: string\n  resultHash: Buffer\n  resultSide: number\n  winner: string\n}\n\nclass PermanentSettleError extends Error\nclass TransientSettleError extends Error\n```\n\n**Export Function**: `settleMatch(deps: SettleTxDeps, pda: string): Promise<SettleResult>` (Lines 129-279)\n\n**Steps**:\n\n1. Retrieve secret from DB (Lines 136-152)\n   - Throw `PermanentSettleError` if not found\n   - Transition \"locked\" → \"settling\" if needed\n   - Log \"settle_submitted\" event\n\n2. Fetch match account from chain (Lines 159-173)\n   - Parse creator (offset 8, 32 bytes)\n   - Parse opponent (offset 40, 32 bytes)\n   - Parse creatorSide (offset 113, 1 byte)\n   - Parse algoVer (offset 147, 1 byte)\n\n3. Fetch config account (Lines 175-187)\n   - Parse treasury (offset 40, 32 bytes)\n\n4. Read entropy from entropy account (Lines 189-194)\n   - First 32 bytes of account data\n\n5. Pre-compute result (Lines 196-200)\n   - `resultHash = SHA256(secret || entropy || matchPda || algoVer)`\n   - `resultSide = resultHash[0] % 2`\n   - `winner = resultSide == creatorSide ? creator : opponent`\n\n6. Derive player profile PDAs (Lines 202-204)\n\n7. Build settle instruction (Lines 206-233)\n   - Discriminator: `[175, 42, 185, 87, 144, 131, 102, 212]`\n   - 40-byte data: discriminator(8) + secret(32)\n   - Accounts: server, match, config, entropy, treasury, creator, opponent, creator_profile, opponent_profile, platform_program, system_program\n\n8. Fetch latest blockhash, build tx, sign with server key (Lines 235-244)\n\n9. Submit & confirm (Lines 246-255)\n\n10. Update DB phase \"settling\" → \"settled\" (Lines 257-264)\n    - Store: settle_tx, result_hash, result_side, winner, settle_attempts\n    - Log \"settle_confirmed\" event\n\n**Constants**:\n- `PLATFORM_PROGRAM_ID` = `\"85qwC1cDpSYkBBHUcN4nuZ119hCx4N94X38GjAHxnWjA\"`\n- `SETTLE_DISCRIMINATOR` = `[175, 42, 185, 87, 144, 131, 102, 212]`\n\n**Account Offsets**:\n- Creator: 8\n- Opponent: 40\n- Creator side: 113\n- Algo version: 147\n\n---\n\n### 15. **Retry Settlement Logic**\n\n**File**: `services/backend/src/worker/retry.ts` — Lines 1-182\n\n**Export**: `createRetrySettler(deps: RetrySettlerDeps): RetrySettler`\n\n**RetrySettler Interface** (Lines 42-50):\n- `attemptSettle(pda: string): Promise<void>` — Attempt settlement with retry logic\n\n**Retry Logic** (Lines 93-178):\n\n1. Skip if PDA already marked as permanently failed or timed out\n2. Check if retry is scheduled but not yet due — skip if so\n3. If max retries (5) exceeded:\n   - Mark as failed\n   - Log \"settle_failed\" event\n   - Return\n4. Check if resolve_deadline (on-chain, offset 156) has passed:\n   - Mark as timeout\n   - Log \"timeout_detected\" event\n   - Return\n5. Attempt `settleMatch(pda)`:\n   - On success: clear retry state, log \"match settled\"\n   - On `PermanentSettleError`: mark failed, log error\n   - On transient error: schedule retry with exponential backoff (base 2s, max 30s)\n\n**Constants**:\n- `MAX_RETRIES` = 5\n- `BASE_DELAY_MS` = 2000\n- `MAX_DELAY_MS` = 30000\n- `RESOLVE_DEADLINE_OFFSET` = 156 (i64 LE in match account)\n\n---\n\n### 16. **Migration Runner**\n\n**File**: `services/backend/src/migrate.ts` — Lines 1-137\n\n**Exports**:\n- `runMigrations(databaseUrl: string): Promise<void>` (Lines 77-102)\n- `showStatus(databaseUrl: string): Promise<void>` (Lines 104-121)\n\n**CLI Usage**:\n- `tsx src/migrate.ts` — Run pending migrations\n- `tsx src/migrate.ts status` — Show migration status\n\n**Behavior** (Lines 60-75):\n1. Ensures `_migrations` tracking table exists\n2. Loads `.sql` files from `../migrations/` directory (sorted by version)\n3. For each pending migration:\n   - Runs SQL in a transaction with `sql.unsafe(content)`\n   - Records version in `_migrations` table\n4. Idempotent: skips already-applied migrations\n\n**Tracking Table**:\n```sql\nCREATE TABLE _migrations (\n  version INT PRIMARY KEY,\n  name TEXT NOT NULL,\n  applied_at TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT now()\n)\n```\n\n---\n\n### 17. **Database Migration**\n\n**File**: `services/backend/migrations/001_init.sql` — Lines 1-36\n\n**Schema**:\n\n**rounds table**:\n```sql\nCREATE TABLE rounds (\n  pda TEXT PRIMARY KEY,\n  game TEXT NOT NULL,\n  creator TEXT NOT NULL,\n  server_key TEXT NOT NULL,\n  secret BYTEA NOT NULL,\n  commitment BYTEA NOT NULL,\n  tier SMALLINT NOT NULL,\n  side SMALLINT NOT NULL,\n  nonce BIGINT NOT NULL,\n  phase TEXT NOT NULL,\n  target_slot BIGINT,\n  settle_tx TEXT,\n  settle_attempts INT DEFAULT 0,\n  result_hash BYTEA,\n  result_side SMALLINT,\n  winner TEXT,\n  created_at TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT now(),\n  updated_at TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT now()\n)\n```\n\n**operator_events table**:\n```sql\nCREATE TABLE operator_events (\n  id BIGSERIAL PRIMARY KEY,\n  pda TEXT,\n  event_type TEXT NOT NULL,\n  payload JSONB,\n  created_at TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT now()\n)\n```\n\n**Indexes**:\n- `idx_rounds_phase` on `rounds(phase)`\n- `idx_rounds_creator` on `rounds(creator)`\n- `idx_operator_events_pda_created` on `operator_events(pda, created_at)`\n- `idx_operator_events_type_created` on `operator_events(event_type, created_at)`\n\n---\n\n## 18. **Test Files**\n\n### 18a. **Auth Middleware Tests**\n\n**File**: `services/backend/src/__tests__/auth.test.ts` — Lines 1-137\n\n**Test Suite**: \"auth middleware\"\n\n**Tests** (total 8):\n1. `accepts a valid signature` (L58-63) — 200 response\n2. `rejects an invalid (zeroed) signature` (L65-71) — 401 response\n3. `rejects a signature from the wrong keypair` (L73-95) — 401 response\n4. `rejects an expired timestamp` (L97-104) — 401 when > 60s old\n5. `accepts a timestamp within clock skew` (L106-113) — 200 when within 60s\n6. `rejects a missing signature field` (L115-121) — 401 response\n7. `rejects a missing timestamp field` (L123-130) — 401 response\n8. `passes GET requests without authentication` (L132-136) — 200 (bypassed auth)\n\n**Helper**: `makeSignedRequest()` constructs canonical payload and signs with tweetnacl\n\n---\n\n### 18b. **Rate Limit Middleware Tests**\n\n**File**: `services/backend/src/__tests__/rate-limit.test.ts` — Lines 1-88\n\n**Test Suite**: \"rate-limit middleware\"\n\n**Tests** (total 7):\n1. `allows requests within per-wallet limit` (L24-30) — 3 requests, all 200\n2. `blocks requests exceeding per-wallet limit` (L32-38) — 2 allowed, 3rd is 429\n3. `returns Retry-After header on per-wallet 429` (L40-46) — Header value = \"60\"\n4. `tracks wallets independently` (L48-60) — Different wallets have separate limits\n5. `enforces global limit across all wallets` (L62-69) — Global limit applies across wallets\n6. `returns correct Retry-After seconds based on window` (L71-77) — 30s window → \"30\" header\n7. `does not rate-limit GET requests` (L79-86) — GET bypasses limiting\n\n---\n\n### 18c. **Fairness Utilities Tests**\n\n**File**: `services/backend/src/__tests__/fairness.test.ts` — Lines 1-105\n\n**Test Suites**: 3 functions tested\n\n**generateSecret tests** (3):\n1. `returns a 32-byte buffer` (L7-11) — Verify length & type\n2. `produces unique secrets on successive calls` (L13-18) — Randomness check\n\n**computeCommitment tests** (5):\n1. `returns sha256 of the secret bytes` (L20-27) — Known SHA256 constant\n2. `matches the packages/fairness commitment algorithm` (L29-43) — Cross-check with Node crypto\n3. `is deterministic` (L45-50) — Same secret → same commitment\n4. `produces different commitments for different secrets` (L52-56) — Different secrets → different commitments\n\n**deriveMatchPda tests** (6):\n1. `returns a PublicKey and bump seed` (L65-71) — Type & range check\n2. `matches manual PDA derivation with seeds [match, creator, nonce_le]` (L73-85) — Cross-check with manual derivation\n3. `accepts bigint nonce` (L87-91) — Both number & bigint accepted\n4. `produces different PDAs for different nonces` (L93-97) — Different nonce → different PDA\n5. `produces different PDAs for different creators` (L99-104) — Different creator → different PDA\n\n---\n\n### 18d. **HTTP Endpoint Tests**\n\n**File**: `services/backend/src/__tests__/endpoints.test.ts` — Lines 1-379\n\n**Fixtures**:\n- Mock Connection class (Lines 46-57)\n- Test constants: `DATABASE_URL`, `TIER_IRON`, `SIDE_HEADS`\n- Auth helper: `signCreateRequest()` (Lines 63-77)\n\n**Test Suite**: \"HTTP endpoint tests\" (3 nested suites)\n\n**POST /fairness/coinflip/create tests** (5):\n1. `returns 200 with valid auth` (L167-189) — Verify response shape\n2. `returns 401 with invalid signature` (L191-208) — Wrong keypair signature\n3. `returns 401 with expired timestamp` (L210-226) — 120s in past\n4. `returns 409 with duplicate nonce` (L228-254) — Same nonce twice\n5. `returns 429 when rate limit exceeded` (L256-285) — Limit 2 per wallet, 3rd blocked\n\n**GET /fairness/rounds/:pda tests** (2):\n1. `returns 200 for known PDA` (L293-325) — Full response shape check, secret redacted for unsettled\n2. `returns 404 for unknown PDA` (L327-334) — Error response\n\n**GET /health tests** (2):\n1. `returns 200 with expected fields` (L342-357) — All response fields present & types correct\n2. `reflects unsettled round count` (L359-377) — Count increments after creating round\n\n---\n\n### 18e. **Integration Test**\n\n**File**: `services/backend/src/__tests__/integration.test.ts` — Lines 1-562\n\n**Test Suite**: \"Integration: create → join → settle lifecycle\"\n\n**Mock Connection Class** (Lines 49-172):\n- Simulates on-chain state in-memory\n- Methods: `setAccount()`, `removeAccount()`, `getLatestBlockhash()`, `getSlot()`, `getAccountInfo()`, `getProgramAccounts()`, `sendRawTransaction()`, `confirmTransaction()`, `getBalance()`\n- Supports memcmp filters for querying accounts by field values\n\n**Account Data Builders** (Lines 177-227):\n- `buildMatchAccountData()` — 246-byte CoinflipMatch account with all fields\n- `buildConfigAccountData()` — 74-byte CoinflipConfig with treasury address\n\n**Tests** (4):\n1. `full lifecycle: create → join (mock) → settle → verify` (L327-500)\n   - Create round via POST /fairness/coinflip/create\n   - Verify DB state in \"created\" phase\n   - Simulate on-chain join by adding PHASE_LOCKED match to mock\n   - Trigger settlement worker poll\n   - Verify DB transitioned to \"settled\" with result data\n   - Verify operator event trail includes all events\n   - Verify GET /fairness/rounds/:pda now includes secret & verification\n\n2. `GET /rounds/:pda returns 404 for unknown PDA` (L502-506) — 404 response\n\n3. `unsettled round does not expose secret` (L508-532) — Secret & verification redacted for \"created\" phase\n\n4. `duplicate nonce returns 409` (L534-561) — Second request with same nonce → 409\n\n---\n\n## Summary Table\n\n| Component | File | Key Exports | Lines |\n|-----------|------|-------------|-------|\n| **Config** | `config.ts` | `Config`, `loadConfig()` | 1-60 |\n| **DB Client** | `db.ts` | `Db`, `Round`, `OperatorEvent`, `RoundPhase`, `createDb()` | 1-224 |\n| **Logger** | `logger.ts` | `logger`, `LogLevel` | 1-43 |\n| **Auth Middleware** | `middleware/auth.ts` | `createAuthMiddleware()` | 1-82 |\n| **Rate Limit Middleware** | `middleware/rate-limit.ts` | `createRateLimitMiddleware()` | 1-93 |\n| **TX Builder** | `tx-builder.ts` | `buildCreateMatchTx()`, `BuildCreateMatchTxResult` | 1-127 |\n| **Fairness Utils** | `fairness.ts` | `generateSecret()`, `computeCommitment()`, `deriveMatchPda()`, `COINFLIP_PROGRAM_ID` | 1-35 |\n| **Coinflip Routes** | `routes/create.ts` | `createCoinflipRoutes()` | 1-180 |\n| **Rounds Routes** | `routes/rounds.ts` | `createRoundsRoutes()` | 1-69 |\n| **Health Routes** | `routes/health.ts` | `createHealthRoutes()` | 1-72 |\n| **Settlement Worker** | `worker/settlement.ts` | `createSettlementWorker()`, `SettlementWorker` | 1-134 |\n| **Settle TX** | `worker/settle-tx.ts` | `settleMatch()`, `SettleResult`, `PermanentSettleError`, `TransientSettleError` | 1-302 |\n| **Retry Settler** | `worker/retry.ts` | `createRetrySettler()`, `RetrySettler` | 1-182 |\n| **Migrations** | `migrate.ts` | `runMigrations()`, `showStatus()` | 1-137 |\n| **SQL Migration** | `migrations/001_init.sql` | `rounds`, `operator_events` tables | 1-36 |\n\n---\n\n## Key Architectural Insights\n\n1. **3-Layer Request Flow**:\n   - Rate limit → Auth signature verification → Route handler\n\n2. **Database-Centric Settlement**:\n   - DB stores secrets (created phase)\n   - Worker detects locked matches on-chain\n   - Settler reads secret from DB, computes result, submits settlement tx\n   - Retry logic with exponential backoff (2s-30s, max 5 attempts)\n\n3. **Phase Machine** (4 states):\n   - `created` → `locked` (detected on-chain)\n   - `locked` → `settling` (settlement starting)\n   - `settling` → `settled` (confirmation received)\n   - `created` → `expired` (timeout fallback)\n\n4. **Audit Trail**:\n   - All state changes logged to `operator_events` table with timestamps & payloads\n   - Enables debugging & fairness verification\n\n5. **Cryptographic Primitives**:\n   - Secret: 32-byte random (generated server-side)\n   - Commitment: SHA256(secret) (shared with client)\n   - Result: SHA256(secret || entropy || pda || algoVer) (derived during settlement)\n\n6. **On-Chain Program IDs**:\n   - Coinflip: `BdHFeqmkYe7znXV1Avk3zz496Pjo8QhEDN4MKPUTAWwx`\n   - Platform: `85qwC1cDpSYkBBHUcN4nuZ119hCx4N94X38GjAHxnWjA`\n   - Entropy: SysvarS1otHashes or custom account\n\nThis backend is a fairness-as-a-service system managing the server's role in commit-reveal coinflip games with off-chain secret storage and on-chain settlement."}],"totalDurationMs":177283,"totalTokens":86356,"totalToolUseCount":37,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":12733,"cache_read_input_tokens":65389,"output_tokens":8233,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":12733},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
